title: helen's 10-inch pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Pour into deep, unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until knife comes out clean, approximately 1 hour or longer.

title: canned taco salsa
directions: Cook all ingredients together until done.
Put in jars; seal and steam pack.

title: easy to make rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water. Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Pour 1 cup hot water over creamed mixture and stir.
Cool.
Add yeast and eggs; stir well.
Gradually add flour and knead dough.
Place in bowl, cover and put in refrigerator. Pinch off as needed.
Shape into rolls, brush with melted butter and let rise.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes until brown.
(Will keep in refrigerator several days.)

title: beef or chicken marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add chicken or beef and allow to soak up to 24 hours.

title: hamburger and cabbage casserole
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
In bacon fat, fry rice and chopped onion until light brown.
Set aside.
Boil 3 cups water and add the can of spaghetti sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan, put one layer (4 cups) shredded cabbage, rice and onion mixture, hamburger and 4 more cups of shredded cabbage.
Then pour liquid over top. Lay bacon on top.
Cover and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: dilly oyster crackers
directions: Put first four ingredients into a large bowl, mix well. Add the 2 bags of oyster crackers and coat well. Mix 4 times in one hour. It's ready to eat and enjoy.

title: very good sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add sour cream and flour to mixture gradually, alternating, beginning and ending with flour.
Add boiling water and mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cook cake in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon.
Saute onion and bell pepper in bacon grease. Add beans.
Add mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Stir well. Cook over low heat for 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed on box.
Drain; mix all ingredients together.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: okra tomato dish
directions: Slice okra and onion in rings.
Dice pepper and add to corn and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly for about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour sauce for dipping
directions: (Recipe may be halved.
Easy to make and much better than fast-food dipping sauce!)

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs,
sugar and flour together.
Add the Karo syrup, pecans, butter
and
vanilla.
Pour
into
unbaked
pie shell. Bake slowly until firm, about 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: saltine cracker cake
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add cream of tartar; beat.
Add sugar; beat until it forms a peak.
Add crushed crackers, vanilla and pecans. Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Pour into buttered dish.
Mix the brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter. Pour over all the boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candied chicken wings
directions: Place wings in a shallow baking pan (cookie sheet or pan about 1-inch deep).
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; sift spices with the flour.
Mix well and add the squash, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas. Place in large container and put in freezer. Keep stirred until mixture gets icy. Add bananas just before serving.

title: chicken adobe
directions: Arrange chicken in skillet on top of stove.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and let bubble gently until chicken is tender (about 40 minutes).

title: stewed peas
directions: Cut, chop or dice onion and garlic; put in pot with large pieces of green pepper, celery leaves and cloves.
Saute in margarine.
Pour black-eyed peas with juice.
Season with enough curry to taste and color (not too yellow), garlic powder and a little black pepper.
Let simmer down, stirring periodically.
Let water dry out without burning; remove green pepper and celery leaves before serving.
Serve over plain rice or separately.

title: sliced baked potato
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough; otherwise, just scrub and rinse them.
Pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use the handle of a spoon to keep knife from cutting all the way.
(Potatoes should look like a fan or an accordian.)
After slicing, put potatoes in baking dish, fanning them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for approximately 50 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until potatoes are soft inside.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except the fruit to a crumble stage.
Pour the fruit in a pan and spread the crust mix over the fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: sourdough waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Let stand at room temperature overnight.
Next a.m., bake on waffle iron.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together nuts, sugar, Karo and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes. Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well and cook 1 to 2 minutes more. Add baking soda and stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: egg salad(club member: john waters)
directions: Cube eggs. Add next 4 ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: artichoke chili dip
directions: Mix together.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: forever ambers
directions: Add all ingredients in glass casserole dish, stirring well. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak crumbs in milk; add
remaining ingredients and mix well. Pack into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan to shape. Invert on shallow baking pan.
Score diagonally with handle of wooden spoon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread ketchup on top and bake 15 more minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and brown sugar in mixer.
Add hot peanut butter (the jar can be placed with lid sealed tight in hot water to warm).
Blend well then add hot butter and vanilla.
Press into the bottom of a pan.
Chill in refrigerator.
When thoroughly cold, cut into squares.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir with wooden spoon until well blended.
Pour into a
13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab melt-a-way
directions: Slice muffins in half, then in quarters.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on muffin quarter; freeze for at least 30 minutes.
Remove from freezer and place under broiler until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs. Add 3/4 cup pizza sauce, cheese, bread crumbs, garlic salt and pepper. Mix well. Combine beef and sausage; add to egg mixture and mix well. Press in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Drain and spoon remaining pizza sauce over meat loaf. Bake 15 minutes more or until no pink remains. Let stand 8 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: surf and turf kabobs
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Set aside.
Diagonally cut summer squash or zucchini into 1-inch slices.
In a saucepan, cook squash and onions in a small count of boiling water, about 1 minute or until almost tender.
Drain.

title: gourmet crab ring
directions: Pour 1/4 cup water over gelatin to soften.
Heat over low flame until dissolved.
Beat in cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in next four ingredients.
Then add pepper and parsley.
Pour into a 3-cup ring mold.
Chill at least 4 hours or until set.
Unmold and garnish with parsley.
Serve with Nabisco Escort crackers or any other mild-flavored cracker.

title: killer cheese cake
directions: Crush the graham crackers.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and melted butter to crumbs.
Press crust into cheese cake pan.
Bake crust for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Mix all together. Be sure to season with salt and pepper. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Grated cheese on top to finish as it will melt.

title: chocolate chip cookies(makes 6 dozen large cookies)
directions: Cream together butter/margarine and the sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat 3 minutes with mixer.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat together.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Don't beat.
(Secret:
Cover cookie sheets with aluminum foil or use "our bake" cookie sheets.)
Drop dough by spoonful (tablespoon) onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: easy peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and flour.
Arrange peaches in crust.
Pour sugar mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon and vanilla together until creamy.
Pour jello into this mixture and blend together.
Pour 1 can chilled (very cold) Pet milk into large mixing bowl and whip until very stiff, then fold jello mixture into the whipped Pet milk.

title: cooked eggnog
directions: In large saucepan mix eggs, milk and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mix coats metal spoon.
Remove from heat.
Quickly cool by placing pan in sink or bowl of cold water, stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: chili salad
directions: In a saucepan, add chili and salsa.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Crush chips; place on a large dish.
Spoon chili mix onto chips.
Next, add lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.

title: mama's spoon bread
directions: Scald cornmeal with 2 cups of milk until thickened.
Add 1 unbeaten egg and stir until absorbed.
Beat 1 egg and 1/2 cup milk together.
Pour corn mixture into a greased dish (I use a loaf-sized glass baking dish).
Pour the 1/2 cup of milk and egg over the corn mixture and cut with a knife.
Bake in a 400° oven sides and top are brown, about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Add enough water until right consistency.
Ice cake.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Keep the popped corn warm in a 200° oven.
Melt the caramels in the top of a double boiler over simmering water.
Add the corn syrup and water and mix until smooth.
Slowly pour over the popcorn; stir to mix well.
With greased hands, shape into balls about the size of softballs.
Let the balls cool and dry completely before wrapping.
Wrap in plastic wrap and tie with string or ribbon.
Makes about 15 balls.

title: shrimp in puree of potato soup
directions: Pare potatoes; cook in boiling salted water until tender. Drain and mash smooth.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Add parsley, potato water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 to 12 minutes, but do not boil.
Add shrimp and heat to boiling.
Serves 4.

title: bake sale brownies
directions: Line the bottom and sides of a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with a sheet of foil.
Mix until blended with wooden spoon butter, sugars and syrup.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Melt chocolate. Stir into sugar mixture.
Add flour mixture and stir until smooth. Add nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; cool. Refrigerate.
Invert onto board and cut into 30 brownies.

title: salmon salad sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, dill weed, salt and pepper until smooth. Add the salmon, carrot and celery. Mix well. Place a lettuce leaf on each bun with salmon.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion, cook until tender.
Drain off fat.
Blend
flour,
salt,	paprika and pepper into meat; stir
in soup.
Simmer,
covered, for about 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in sour cream; heat.
Spoon into toasted buns.

title: texas fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch pan.
Put layer of Monterey Jack cheese.
Spread green chilies over layer of cheese.
Put Colby cheese on top of chilies.
Beat 6 eggs well; pour over all.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Cut into cubes.
Serve on crackers or alone.

title: sour cream chocolate pound cake
directions: Whip butter and add sugar.
Beat together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to mix along with sour cream.
Add boiling water after each addition.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Be sure to grease and flour pan.
Ice and decorate with buttercream icing when cooled.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix lightly.
Form into loaf and place in loaf pan.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco sauce.
Spread this on the bottom of your dish or pan.
Then spread a layer of refried beans.
Refrigerate until firm.
Then spread a layer of diced onions, diced tomatoes and the shredded cheese and lettuce last, so that the lettuce won't get mushy.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables until tender; drain.
Mix vegetables, celery, onion and mayonnaise and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fancy sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mash potatoes, sugar, spices and butter together.
Use ice cream scoop.
Scoop one ball of mixture into center of each pineapple ring.
Place maraschino cherry in center of each scoop and place 3 or 4 marshmallows on potato.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes on cookie sheet.
These can be made ahead and baked and served later.

title: bratwurst preparation
directions: Put all ingredients in skillet with enough water to cover bratwurst.
Pierce bratwurst.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Grill bratwurst normally.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and press into pan.
Chill in freezer while you make filling.

title: healthy heart soup(low calorie)
directions: Cut everything into small-medium pieces.
Place in large stew pot; cover with water.
Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes. Reduce heat and simmer until done.
"May be packed in jars while hot and canned."

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, and Karo.
Boil over medium heat in skillet until honey colored and peanuts begin to pop (15 to 20 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Beat vigorously. Work fast and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add egg yolks and mix well. Add buttermilk, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites and pour in three 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot-pineapple-raisin salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In a bowl, stir together carrots, pineapple (with juice) and raisins.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: baltimore crab cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Shape into cakes or patties. Fry until brown.

title: golden bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread cubes in buttered 9-inch square baking dish.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour evenly over bread cubes, completely moistening bread.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve warm or chilled.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: corn and pea salad
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients together.
Let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to cool mixture.
Refrigerate and let set for 4 hours.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Blend cheese, mayonnaise, garlic and pimento.
Clean celery. Let celery stand in ice water for 1 hour.
Drain and fill center of celery.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Put strawberries, Kool-Aid and lemonade in blender.
Blend. Put in large bowl; put sugar and water in pan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool; add rest of ingredients.
Freeze.
To serve, add frozen slush and soda.

title: gob cake
directions: After layers of cake cool; cut layers horizontally to half thickness.
Bring to a boil milk.
Sift flour into hot milk, stirring until it becomes paste mixture.
Refrigerate until cool. Whip margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add cooled flour paste.
Beat at high speed at least 10 minutes.
Add vanilla. Spread on all four layers.
The sides need not be iced.

title: tomato basil platter
directions: Place slices of tomato alternately with basil leaves on a large platter.
Whisk together the olive oil and red wine vinegar and pour over the tomatoes.
Top with freshly ground pepper and salt to taste. Cover lightly with plastic wrap and allow to stand at room temperature about 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand first. Then add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Refrigerate and serve.

title: cheese straws
directions: Have margarine and cheese at room temperature.
Cream margarine and cheese; add flour, salt and pepper slowly.
You may use cookie press or roll out and cut into desired lengths.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Do not let them brown.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spice together.
Add buttermilk and
flour alternately.
Stir in preserves.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.
Cook at	350°
until tested done.
Use your favorite icing.

title: chicken bog
directions: Boil chicken in large pot in 5 cups water until tender. Remove chicken and break into small pieces. Measure broth and add enough water to make 5 1/2 cups. Add sausage, onion, salt and peppers. Return to boil for 10 minutes. Add chicken and rice. Cook on low heat for 25 minutes or until rice is done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill 3 hours before serving.

title: dad's citrus punch
directions: Mix first four ingredients together. Add ginger ale just before serving. Perfect party punch.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine flour, salt, lemon peel and 1/4 c. sugar. Cut in oleo. Combine eggs, milk & yeast. Add to flour mixture. Combine lightly. Cover tightly. Refrigerate overnight. Divide dough in half. Roll on floured surface to 18 X 12 rectangle. Spread each half with 1/2 c. sugar and cinnamon mixture. Roll up tightly. Cut in 1 inch slices. Place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with palm of hand. Bake at 400 degrees for 15-18 minutes. Drizzle with icing. Makes 36 rolls.

title: fried chicken and milk gravy
directions: Cut chicken breast in two parts.
Blend salt, pepper and flour.
Dredge chicken pieces, working flour into each piece, leaving no moist spots to spatter and lose juice.
In heavy skillet (with lid), melt butter and Crisco on medium heat.	Place meaty pieces in skillet first; slip in slimmer parts as they brown.
Don't crowd pieces.
Brown well on one side; with fork or tongs, turn and brown other side of chicken pieces.
Do not pierce chicken.
Place in baking dish or pan.
Add 2 tablespoons water to baking dish; cover with foil and place in oven at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.
When you cut thickest part to the bone, no pink should show.
For crisp chicken, uncover last 15 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings in mixture for 2 days.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Line baking pan with aluminum foil.
Remove chicken wings from marinade and place in baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour, turning halfway and basting with the marinade.
Enjoy!

title: wiener appetizers
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1-inch pieces; cut canned biscuits into 3 sections.
Wrap each section around piece of hot dog.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Provide dishes of mustard and catsup to dip them in.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut and drain all fruit mix and put in large bowl.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over fruit.
Do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir when ready to serve.

title: crackly ginger cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients. Chill and roll into balls.
Drop quickly in ice water, then sugar. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry-coconut dessert
directions: Combine the cake mix and margarine, beating well.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Press remaining mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread cherry pie filling over crust and sprinkle coconut over this. Sprinkle reserved cake mix over coconut and bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bean and rice soup
directions: In a large pan, cook and stir meat, onion and celery until tender.
Add water, beans, tomato sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Replace cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cheese and cream with peanut butter.
Slowly add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and beat until creamy and smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch prepared crust (graham cracker or chocolate crumb).
Cover and refrigerate.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in concentrate, cranberry
juice and water.
Place in large bowl or molded ice ring.
Makes 35 servings.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Wash the cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Combine cauliflower and next 3 ingredients into a medium mixing bowl; toss gently.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Stir well.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: october pie
directions: Mix - keep one cup aside.
Press the rest into bottom of pan.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake per package directions in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix the small can of crushed pineapple and sugar in a pan and bring to a boil, cooking approximately 5 minutes.
Poke holes on top of hot cake and pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Mix instant pudding according to directions and spread over top of cooled cake.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice thin.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Chill and serve.
Serves 4.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix burger, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape into 12 balls.
Cook in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: shish-k-bobs
directions: Tenderize meat by pounding with edge of saucer or using prepared tenderizer such as Lawry's.
Scrub vegetables and slice into about 1/4-inch slices.
Leave okra whole.
Alternate meat cubes with vegetables on bamboo skewers.
Amounts of vegetables are determined by your family's likes and dislikes.
Place skewers into two 8 x 11-inch greased baking dishes.
Three skewers will fit into each dish.
Dot with butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1/2 canned tomatoes into each dish.
Place 1/2 bottle liquid smoke over each dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This dish can be prepared ahead and baked later in the day.
Serve with salad and bread for a complete meal.

title: nut tassies
directions: Make the crust by mixing the margarine, cream cheese and flour.
Make into small balls.
Roll out each ball to line small muffin tins.
Make the filling by beating the eggs, brown sugar, melted margarine and vanilla together.
Sprinkle a few chopped pecans into shells; fill with sugar and egg mixture.
Place a pecan on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 250° for 10 minutes.

title: spicy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine first, then add other ingredients and simmer until cheese melts.

title: simple crumb cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and combine with cinnamon and nuts.
Set aside.

title: broccoli cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, pour the bag of broccoli slaw mix.
In another bowl, mix cole slaw mix (dry) as directed on package. Pour dressing over broccoli slaw mix; mix well.
Before serving, sprinkle cheese and bacon on top.

title: yahba-dabba doo squares
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 24 squares.

title: fried rice
directions: Lay bacon slices over heating base in wok; set heat control to medium-high.
Fry bacon until crisp (about 6 minutes).
Remove bacon; drain on paper towel and crumble.
With bacon drippings in wok, stir-fry onion for 2 minutes.
Add rice and stir-fry for 7 to 8 minutes.
Add soy sauce, water and crumbled bacon.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Pour eggs on top of rice mixture.
Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until eggs are cooked.
Reduce heat to low for serving.
Makes 4 servings. Recipe may be doubled.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter; beat in egg.
Mix all other ingredients in.
Pour into greased cake pan or 2-quart bowl.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble all of the cornbread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add all of the beans, spreading them over the entire pan.
Add a layer of green peppers, layer of onion, layer of dill pickles and then layer of tomatoes.
Mix together 1/2 cup pickle vinegar and 3 cups mayonnaise.
Spread this on top of everything. You can serve it like this or you can crumble the bacon up on top of the mayonnaise mixture.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put oleo in skillet and let it melt.
Mix the flour in and let bubble good.
Pour in broth; let come to a boil.
Add milk.
Cut up eggs and put in casserole dish.
Add chicken.
Pour the flour mixture over this and cover with rolled real thin biscuits.
Bake at 400°.

title: linguini with clam sauce white
directions: Cover the bottom of a saucepan with oil.
Add chopped garlic; saute until golden in color.
Add seasonings.
Stir in clams, clam juice and parsley.
Simmer until clams are heated through, about 5 minutes.
Boil linguini; strain.
Add sauce.

title: potato bake
directions: Bake for 45 minutes with foil on and for 10 minutes, uncovered, in a 400° oven.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix Philadelphia cream cheese, juice of lemon and condensed milk together.
Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Set in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Open cherries and pour on top of pie. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put hash browns in bottom of baking pan.
Mix hash browns, soup, cheese, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix all of that together.
Put in dish, then put melted butter and bread crumbs together for the top of hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add small amounts at a time to creamed mixture.
Add raisins, oats and raisin juice and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine melted butter and brown sugar and spread evenly on bottom of 9-inch round cake pan.
Next, place whole pineapple slice with cherry in hole in center of pan.
Arrange whole or half pineapple slices on remaining area of pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening, add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift flour, measure and sift again with baking soda.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture, stir in vanilla, then coconut and chopped nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 inch pans or two 9 inch pans.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees and bake for 25 minutes, or cake tests done.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes and turn out on racks to cool, then frost.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion. Mix all ingredients and dry seasonings and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: never fail peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until threads spin.
Then add peanuts and stir continuously; after peanuts are brownish gold, take from fire.
Add butter, salt and soda.
Pour onto buttered board to cool.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix together everything and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Blend and chill.
Serve in a hollowed out loaf of bread.
Dip the bread pieces.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 5 minutes (follow instructions on package). Mash enough strawberries to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan. Stir in water and strawberries gradually. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute. Cool.

title: cranberry-apple mold
directions: Dissolve raspberry flavored gelatin in boiling water; let cool. Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly oiled 4-cup mold. Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hawaiian carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry
ingredients
in
a large bowl.
In a large bowl with
a
mixer, beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.	Then add pineapple,	carrots,
coconut
and raisins.
Mix with dry ingredients,
only until blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or a Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for about 60 minutes.

title: chocolate or coconut delight
directions: Combine flour, pecans and melted butter.
Mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Mix together instant pudding mix and milk.
Chill 5 minutes.
Spread over coconut.
Cover this with one 8 ounce Cool Whip.
Top with coconut.
Chill 4 hours.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour into baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes more at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm, if desired.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Combine lemon-flavored gelatin and one cup boiling water in small bowl, stirring mixture 2 minutes or until gelatin is dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to gelatin.
Chill gelatin until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.

title: sauteed squash, mushrooms and collard greens
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet.
Add squash, mushrooms, lemon pepper, garlic and union; saute until tender, then add collard greens and stir-fry until wilted.
Remove and salt to taste.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Drain.
Put potatoes in buttered casserole dish.
Then crumble corned beef on top.
Top with cheese.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients, except nuts, thoroughly.
Add nuts and blend well throughout mixture. Pour the plum cake mixture into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake in the oven for 45 to 50 minutes until a toothpick comes clean after inserting it in the middle of the cake.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and cool.
Combine ingredients and marinate at least 24 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients except dressing.
Add dressing just before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Mix and freeze; serve with Sprite.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spread in 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange peaches in pie plate, reserving and chopping several for topping.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach juice in bowl; mix well.
Spread over peaches.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Arrange reserved chopped peaches over cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in microwave pan.
Slice margarine on top. Pour on 1/4 cup milk, but do not mix.
Cover and cook in microwave for 2 minutes at Full power.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir to mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square dish.
Chill 1 hour.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Butter a 1-quart long Pyrex dish.
Layer peas, eggs and cheese.
Pour diluted soup on top.
Sprinkle with wheat germ. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Allow to set a few minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french silk pie
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix in vanilla and chocolate.
Add eggs (one at a time), beating after each addition, for 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream and chill.

title: hopping johns
directions: In large sauce pan cooke peas according to pkg.
instructions until almost done; add remaining ingredients and simmer untile peas are tender, about 30 minutes.
Add warm water untile there is enough pot liquor.
Serve with cornbread and slaw.
(This is a tradition at the Stoker's on New Year's Day.)

title: spanish delight
directions: Heat oil and add onions and peppers.
Simmer until tender then add ground beef, tomato paste, mushrooms, corn chili sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook the noodles, drain and give cold water bath, mix with meat mixture and put in casserole to bake.
Put on top of the mixture, the Longhorn cheese and dot with stuffed sliced olives.

title: shrimp crunch
directions: Drain shrimp and water chestnuts.
Arrange sliced water chestnuts on serving plate.
Put a dab of mayonnaise on each slice.
Top with 1 shrimp each.

title: *cranberry jello mold
directions: Grind in a food grinder (perhaps a blender), the first 6 ingredients.
When completed, add 1 1/2 cups sugar to mixture. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add mixture to jello and mold.

title: paprikas potatoes
directions: Put sliced sausage and onion in Dutch oven. Brown until onion is transparent. Add paprika, sliced potatoes, salt and pepper (to taste). Add water and cover, cooking over medium heat. Cook until potatoes are tender. Add more water, if necessary. Serves 4.

title: chili cheese log rolls
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature. Blend both.
Blend in rest of ingredients, except the chili powder.
Form into two log rolls and sprinkle chili powder on log rolls.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Can be frozen up to 3 months.

title: easy quiche
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; gradually add soup and cream.
Mix well.
Sprinkle cheese, meat and vegetables evenly over pie crust. Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable dish for 6
directions: Layer in a 8 1/2 x 14-inch baking dish:
frozen vegetables, water chestnuts, cheese, crackers and butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: short cut pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Sift into an 8 or 9-inch pie tin.
Whip oil and milk together and pour over flour mixture.
Mix with a fork until all flour is moistened.
Save out 1/3 cup of dough for top.
Press dough evenly in pie pan covering bottom and sides.
Crimp edges.
Add fruit filling.
Crumble reserved dough over top.
Bake as fruit pie recipe directs.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Place pasta in bowl.
Add turkey, celery, onion and green pepper; toss to mix.
Combine dressing mix, sour cream, salad dressing and garlic salt.
Add to pasta mixture and mix well. Garnish with tomato slices and pepper rings, if desired.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar.
Cut shortening into flour; add yeast mixture and buttermilk and stir to form a soft dough.
On a floured board, knead a few times and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and place on greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until nicely browned. Yield:
35 biscuits.

title: oatmeal cookie of the year
directions: Beat butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and mix.
Add raisins and all other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Add boiling water; cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add pinch of salt.
On high speed, gradually add sugar and beat until peaks form.
On low speed, add vanilla and cornstarch mixture. Return to high speed and beat until stiff.
Cover pie filling. Bake at 375°.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Melt margarine and put in separate bowl.
Mix cheese and bread crumbs with remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken in margarine, then in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
When halfway cooked, pour 1/2 cup dry vermouth on top of chicken.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix in Veg-All, soups, broth and onion.
Pour into buttered dish.
Roll out crescent rolls and spread out on top.
Bake at 350° until rolls are brown.

title: pork and rice with gravy
directions: Brown and cook pork slightly, all around, at 300°.
Take pork out of pan and add cream of mushroom soup, water, cooking sherry and Lipton onion soup mix.
Mix until all ingredients are mixed well.
Add pork chops; cover all sides with gravy.
Cover and cook at about 300°, stirring and flipping pork chops occasionally.
If gravy gets too thick, add a little more water.
Cook until pork is 165° with a meat thermometer.
Make rice on the side.
Serve pork and rice with gravy on top.

title: almond rice
directions: Combine water, broth and salt in a saucepan; bring to a boil and add rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed.
Melt butter in a small skillet.
Saute almonds in butter until lightly browned.
Stir into rice.

title: potato supreme
directions: Cook potatoes in skin.	Peel when done.
Let stand in fridge overnight.	Shred cooked potatoes.	Stir in other ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain, peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Put into serving bowl.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let cool at least 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned custard ice cream
directions: Cook well beaten eggs and 2 quarts of milk over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture coats wooden spoon.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Be sure all sugar is dissolved.
Mixture should be a little too sweet and taste like it has a little too much flavor as it loses some of its sweetness and flavor in the freezing.
Cool thoroughly before freezing.
Freeze according to freezer directions.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 gallons.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing mix and margarine.
Mix stuffing mix and margarine together.
Line bottom of casserole with 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Pour in ingredients.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: onion corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into greased, heated muffin pans.
Cook 15 minutes at 400° and 15 minutes at 500°. This mixture will keep in refrigerator without onion for up to 2 weeks.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread on platter the bean dip.
Mix and spread on top the avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix and spread on top the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Sprinkle with green onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with round chips.

title: saucepan cookies
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt and cook until sugar dissolves. Blend in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine chopped ingredients in a bowl.
In a large bowl, mix 1/2 cornbread, 1/2 chopped ingredients and 1/2 mayonnaise mixture. When thoroughly mixed, add remainder of ingredients and mix well. Mix in some Bac*Os.
Chill.
Best if prepared a day ahead and allowed to stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: spicy tomato halves(microwave)
directions: Core tomatoes, cut in half crosswise.
Arrange in baking dish. Saute onions in butter in shallow dish in microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in bread cubes and spices.
Divide mixture evenly over tomato halves.
Cook, covered, in microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes.
Turn dish halfway through the cooking time. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hobo dinner
directions: In large casserole dish press ground beef (or turkey) to bottom of dish.
Slice potatoes and put on top of meat.
Mix soup and milk and pour over meat and potatoes.
Place cheese slices over all this.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: orange delight
directions: Gently fold cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and dry gelatin into prepared topping.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Coat meat in flour and brown lightly in a little fat in a heavy skillet. Lift meat out of skillet into a casserole.
Add drained mushrooms. Sprinkle with soup mix and pepper.
Add water to mushroom liquid to make 1 cup and pour into casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until meat is tender, stirring once during the cooking.
Remove from oven and stir sour cream into piping hot mixture.
Serve at once over hot noodles or rice. Serves 6.

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine soup, grated cheese, mayonnaise and egg.
Pour over broccoli.
Top broccoli with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruited dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend well. Dip your choice of fruit: banana, apples, strawberry or pineapple.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail well.
Soften cream cheese.
Combine all ingredients.
Freeze until firm.

title: ethel's sweet relish
directions: Add relish mixture.
Boil hard for 3 minutes and seal in jars. Makes approximately 8 pints.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in cold water, salt and pineapple with syrup.
Chill until slightly thickened, but not set.
Stir in carrots.
Pour into a 4-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.

title: pasta fagiole
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook

garlic, stirring until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Stir in broth and tomatoes with their juices and bring to a boil, breaking up tomatoes with a fork. Add beans, pasta, 2 tablespoons basil and Parmesan and boil, stirring frequently, until pasta is al dente. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. (Pasta will continue to absorb liquid.)
Stir in remaining tablespoon basil and pepper to taste. Drizzle with remaining tablespoon oil and serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except croutons.
Place in greased 2-quart baking dish and sprinkle croutons on top.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles all over.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk and butter to very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid, almond extract and egg.
Blend until smooth.
Stir into mixture remaining ingredients and 2 cups flour to form stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Roll into 12 x 7-inch oval.
Fold over long side to 1/2 inch opposite side. Cover; let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool; drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, milk, bread crumbs, garlic, onion, celery and cheese together.
Add mixture to hamburg.
Knead the loaf or loaves until meat is tight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: garlic herb butter
directions: In a sealable container, place butter that has been softened. Add the rest of the ingredients to individual taste.
Makes great garlic bread.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Spread the jars of picante sauce over first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle lettuce, tomatoes and cheese over top.
Use tortilla chips to dip into mixture.

title: biscotti(italian dessert cookie)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, except sugar.
Cream sugar with butter; add eggs, one at a time, and mix.
Add extract and raisins.
Carefully add dry mixture to sugar mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to directions on package. Melt cheese in hot rice.
Add broccoli and soup to rice mixture. Wilt onion and celery in 1 stick of butter.
Mix all ingredients together; sprinkle bread crumbs on top, if desired, and bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: curried chicken thighs
directions: Heat margarine until hot.
Lightly brown chicken on both sides.
Transfer to shallow baking dish.
Saute onion and apple in drippings in same skillet.
Stir in flour, curry and salt.
Cook, stirring, for about 30 seconds, then stir in tomato paste, lemon juice, cayenne and ginger.
Whisk in chicken broth until smooth. Cook, stirring, until thickened and bubbly.
Spoon half of the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Spoon remaining sauce over chicken and bake 20 minutes more.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Dredge chop with flour.
Brown on both sides in Crisco. Remove chops and replace with peppers, onions and chili sauce. Add other ingredients.
Cook gently until tender.
Add chops; cover and cook slowly 45 minutes.

title: canned okra
directions: Bring to boil for 10 minutes.
Pack in jars; seal.
When you eat it, rinse off, drain and fry.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup, together.
Shape into balls. Brown in frying pan.
Put in baking dish.
Stir in tomato soup. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or heated through.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Warm oil; add the remaining ingredients and whip together until smooth.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix together Ricotta cheese, egg, basil, salt, pepper and 1/2 to 3/4 pound of the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Set aside.
Cook macaroni until al dente.
Drain and rinse briefly.
Place macaroni in oven-safe baking dish.
Add Ricotta cheese mixture and sauce to macaroni and mix well.
Sprinkle remaining shredded Mozzarella over ziti.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: volcano punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine pineapple juice and lemonade.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and add scoops of sherbet. Garnish with fresh fruit.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: pickled onions
directions: Place onions in a nonmetallic bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add cold water to cover onions.
Stand for 24 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the sugar and eggs.
Add pineapple and carrots. Sift dry ingredients into this.
Mix. Bake in 2 round greased cake pans for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: bay leaf pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Put uncracked eggs in a bowl and pour hot tap water over them.
Let stand several minutes to warm eggs gently.
Crumble 5 of the bay leaves as finely as possible; combine them with the milk in a saucepan, bringing slowly to a simmer, stirring once or twice. Remove from the heat and set aside.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; sift together on a piece of waxed paper or in a bowl.
Beat butter until smooth and creamy.
Continue beating as you add sugar; beat until blended.
Crack warm eggs into batter and beat about 2 minutes until very fluffy.
Sprinkle on half of the flour and beat until smooth.
Strain bay leaves out of the milk and add milk to batter.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour; beat until smooth.
Spread evenly into loaf pan.
Place remaining two bay leaves on top of cake.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely on a rack.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and baking soda.
Combine all ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch glass pan or your choice (Bundt pan or spring-form pan can be used).
(I sometimes use Pam to spray cooking pan before flouring.)
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage; let stand 1 hour and then squeeze out juice.
In a saucepan combine remaining ingredients.
Mix and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture and add 1 teaspoon celery seed and 1 teaspoon mustard seed.
Freeze in containers.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa in pan.
Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour and pecans.
Add cocoa mixture to this and mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
When done, spread marshmallow cream on while warm.
Cool and frost.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Set aside. Cream the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the peanut butter, egg and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Place dough on lightly floured waxed paper.
Roll in a 15 x 8-inch rectangle. Chill.
Melt chocolate.
Cool slightly and spread over dough. Roll like jelly roll. Chill 20 to 30 minutes.
Slice cookies 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: coffee egg nog punch
directions: Combine egg nog, brown sugar, coffee and cinnamon; beat.
Stir in liqueur and chill.
Beat cream with confectioners sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Pour egg nog into punch bowl.
Top with whipped cream and cinnamon.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Mix the sour cream, soda and vanilla separately, then add rest of the ingredients.
These can be cut out or dropped onto pans by teaspoonfuls.
Do not overbake.

title: cantaloupe sherbet
directions: Mix water and honey thoroughly.
Add cantaloupe and blend. Put into freezer tray and freeze.

title: hot crabmeat cocktail dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese, mayonnaise, wine and seasonings.
Pick over crabmeat.
Fold by hand into mayonnaise mixture.
Heat in double boiler.
Serve hot with crackers and toasted party rye bread.
Serves 30.

title: clam dip
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter and saute garlic.
In 8-inch square baking dish, add all remaining ingredients.
Add butter and garlic and mix well.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake in 325° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve as a spread on crackers.

title: holiday billy goats (cookies)(makes 7 to 8 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add flour, soda, salt, spices, sour milk and nuts. Drop 1 teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate for 24 hours.
Cook for 20 minutes on grill or in oven at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together
and
store in Tupperware. For each cup, use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown ground chuck with salt and pepper, brown sugar and onion.
Add tomato soup.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Layer ground chuck mixture with noodle mixture in a casserole dish.
Put processed cheese between the layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place stew meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Put bouillon cubes on meat at each end of casserole, then place a layer of potatoes, layer of carrots, layer of onions, then peas.
Put cream of celery soup in a separate bowl; stir in Kitchen Bouquet, until the color of soup is dark brown, then pour over top of casserole. Do not mix this in until an hour before it's done.
Cover and bake 3 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: manicotti
directions: Saute oil, garlic and onions for 5 minutes.
Mix onion and garlic with all sauce ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: zucchini and tomato
directions: Peel and chop onions.
Saute in butter until soft.
Add tomatoes, peeled and sliced.
Add sliced zucchini on top of onions in a casserole.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Combine herbs, oil, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour over tomatoes and zucchini.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: kebab with eggplant(lebanese)
directions: Peel and cut eggplants lengthwise into 4 pieces, then each quarter in 3 cm long pieces. Soak the eggplant pieces in well salted water for 1/2 hour. Squeeze them and fry them in a frying pan where the butter and some oil have been heated. Remove them from the frying pan and put aside. In the same frying pan, partially cook the meat for 3 to 4 minutes; put all in a saucepan where the kebab will be cooked.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Add mixture.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix 2 cups water with Jell-O and unflavored gelatin (one cold, one hot).
Refrigerate while preparing other ingredients.
Mix together and chill until jelled.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oil and sugars.
Mix well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Again, mix well.
Into sifter, pour flour, salt and soda.
Sift and mix into oil/sugar mixture.
Stir.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop onto cookie sheet by spoonful.
Place at least 1-inch apart. Bake at 350°.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Butter pan.
Mix together sugar and syrup in saucepan, stirring constantly, bring to boil.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl for use of mixer.
Add peanut butter and mix gently using low speed.
Add cereal; mix lightly until cereal is completely coated.
Pour into pan.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy. Ice cake of your choice.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together and store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Several different types of rolls can be made from this one basic sweet dough recipe, simply by varying the final steps of preparation.

title: 100 year old black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add extracts to milk.
Add baking powder to flour.
Alternately add liquid and dry ingredients to batter; stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube or flute pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until cake tests done.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl (add water if needed; don't make too watery).
Put eggplant in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in pan on medium (on top of the stove) or at 350° in electric frypan.
Set aside and make sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook sugar and syrup to 228°.
Beat eggs well.
Add melted butter to syrup.
Add hot syrup slowly to beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake about 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: easy onion soup dip
directions: Dilute the mixture to your own consistency.
Blend or mix until smoothly mixed together.
Dip can be used with many dipables:
vegetables, potato chips and other chips, same as sour cream on baked potatoes.

title: chicken mixed grill
directions: Place chicken in a glass bowl; coat with marinade.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Place beef in a separate container.
Let stand for one hour.
Preheat grill; brush grid with oil.
Place dark meat over direct heat; cover and cook with vents open for 15 minutes. Add white meat; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Place sausages on grill; continue to cook for 10 minutes.
Place beef on skewers and continue to cook for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: curry-cashew carrots
directions: In a
quart saucepan over medium heat in 2 inches of water, heat
carrots and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Reduce heat to low,
cover
and
simmer
15 minutes or until tender-crisp; drain.
Add
butter, curry, cashews, sugar and sherry. Stir and cook
for
a
few
minutes
until piping hot and all ingredients are
well
mixed.
(Leftovers may be blended with milk or cream to make a delicious cream of carrot soup.)

title: sausage, pear and corn bread stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Crumble bread into small pieces; toast until golden, about 35 minutes. Put in a large bowl or place packaged corn bread into a large bowl. Remove sausage from casing. Add sausage and brown over medium heat. Add apple juice; simmer, stirring constantly, until liquid evaporates. Remove sausage to bowl. Set aside. Add oil to skillet. Add onion and celery. Saute until translucent. This is about 8 minutes. Add to bowl. Stir in pears, parsley, thyme, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper. Stir in enough chicken stock to moisten stuffing to your taste. After stuffing turkey breast, bake remaining stuffing in foil covered baking dish about 30 minutes. Remove foil. Continue baking until top turns golden brown, about 15 minutes more.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ritz crackers.
Top with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine.
Pour over the meatballs.
Bake 1 hour at 425°.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Line bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with croutons. Sprinkle with ham and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and spices together in bowl.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to package directions.
Cool and crumble.
Mix in all other ingredients and serve.

title: bran apple muffins
directions: Combine flakes and juice or milk.
Let set 5 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil and egg to flakes mixture, then dry ingredients and chopped apple.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chili con quesa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will vary greatly with brand of chilies.
If melted, then reheated later, more cream will be needed, about 1/4 cup more.
Melt in top of double boiler.
Use as dip for vegetables or crackers.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough in 8 x 12-inch dish; spread to fit dish.
Spread pizza sauce over dough.
Brown sausage; drain and spread over dough and sauce.
Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in leftover grease until transparent; spoon mixture over dough.
Spread cheese, pepperoni and chopped black olives on top. Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Place cookie sheet under 8 x 12-inch pan so pizza won't run over in oven.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and ketchup well.
Add rest of ingredients. This is especially good with raw cauliflower and broccoli.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (glass or metal).
Crumble browned sausage and sprinkle over roll layer.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sausage layer.
(May be covered and refrigerated at this point for later use.)
Combine eggs and milk and add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake at 425° (400° for glass) for 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are well set.
Serves 12.

title: crispy pizza party puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease a 10 x 15 inch baking sheet. Empty the entire contents of the pizza mix (crust mix, sauce and cheese) into a large mixing bowl. Add the sausage, mixing well.
This will be sticky.
Shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Roll the balls in crushed chips.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Yield: about 2 doz.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Place the zucchini, squash, peppers, asparagus and onion in a large roasting pan. Toss with olive oil, salt and pepper to mix and coat. Spread in a single layer in the pan. Roast for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are lightly browned and tender. This has 15 grams carbohydrates.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and drain both dill and cucumbers well.
Sterilize jars and drain.
Pack cucumbers and dill in jars.
If you like, use garlic and hot pepper.

Put the jars of cucumbers in the oven and have them hot to handle before filling jars with vinegar mixture. Bring water, vinegar and salt to a good hard boil and keep boiling while filling jars and cucumbers.
Seal at once.
This makes 7 or 8 quarts of pickles.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water or juice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
To unmold, dip pan in water (warm) for about 15 seconds.
(I usually do not do this.
I just cut into squares and remove with spatula.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Prepare all ingredients and toss all together.
Marinate all night.
Serves 10 to 12 persons and enjoy.

title: fruit filled cake
directions: No water needed.
Mix and bake following directions on box.

title: no-fail meringue
directions: Beat egg whites, water, baking powder and salt until frothy. Add sugar gradually until meringue stands in peaks.
Stir in vanilla.

title: chicken pot pie(serves 6)
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth.
Remove chicken and chop.
Skim fat from broth, reserving 2 cups broth.
Melt margarine; add onion and next 4 ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup flour; stir until smooth.
Add reserved broth and half and half.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in chicken, pepper and thyme. Pour into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.

title: marilyn's tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Add soups and milk.
Place Tater Tots in 2-quart casserole.
Pour beef mixture over top.
Bake uncovered in a 325° to 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: chow mein
directions: Preheat skillet, uncovered, at 325°.
Add ground pork, celery and onions, stir gently and fry until browned, about 5 minutes. Remove excess grease.
Add salt, brown sugar, pepper and reserved mushroom liquid.
Stir to combine.
Cover with vent closed, reduce heat to simmer and cook for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Allow potatoes to partially thaw. In a large mixing bowl, combine potatoes with remaining ingredients; mix well, then spread in lightly buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake 90 minutes. Serve hot.

title: mary fox's ham loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and form into 1 or 2 loaves.
Make a paste of the mustard, brown sugar, flour and vinegar and spread on top of loaf.
Place pineapple on top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: "ramen" noodle stir-fry
directions: Stir 1 package noodle seasoning into raw meat; set aside. Precook vegetables 5 minutes.
Drain and stir in 1 package of seasoning.
Cook all packages of noodles in 6 cups boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain and stir in last package of seasoning; set aside.
Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Brown meat quickly (approximately 5 minutes).
Stir in vegetables and noodles.
Ready to eat!

title: foolproof angel food cake
directions: You will need an angel food cake pan for this recipe.

title: corn chowder
directions: Dice the bacon and put into pan to brown.
Add onion, celery and pepper; fry until bacon is crisp.
Add the corn and saute together for 3 minutes.
Add potatoes, tomatoes and seasoning. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Finally, add the milk.
Heat to the boiling point and serve with a little chopped parsley.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in greased pan.
If fruit is very juicy, mix cornstarch. Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in egg. Add flour and milk alternately.
Pour over fruit in pan. Bake in a 375° oven about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or whipped cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Put 1/2 in bottom of pan (11 x 13-inch).

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients on low 1 minute.
Add Cool Whip. Fold in.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Easy and good.

title: hello dollie
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over to form crust. Sprinkle coconut over graham cracker crust. Sprinkle chocolate morsels over coconut. Sprinkle chopped nuts over chocolate. Pour can of milk over mixture and let set. Bake in oven at 350° until brown. Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and form into 40 bite size balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each.
Brown meatballs lightly in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Combine chili sauce and grape jelly. Pour over meatballs.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until jelly is melted.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes until sauce has thickened, basting occasionally.

title: chicken on top rice
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix well. Arrange chicken pieces skin side up.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and poultry seasoning.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: chelle's pineapple pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Karo and pineapple.
Put into pie crusts. Chill.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer ingredients as follows:
lettuce, cauliflower, bacon, onion, celery, dressing and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Toss and serve.
Serves 12.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream in medium size bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread onto tortilla, then roll up and slice into bite size pieces.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Combine zucchini, sugar, lemon juice and crushed pineapple or juice.
Cook 12 minutes.
Add the apricot jello (after you take it off stove).

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Rinse and cut scallions from green onion.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Make into a round ball and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; remove excess fat. Add next 6 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles; drain. Layer noodles, sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, noodles, Mozzarella, noodles, sauce and top with Mozzarella. Sprinkle with parsley flakes. Repeat layers if needed. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: cathy's zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; slowly add flour, then nuts, zucchini, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Bake in loaf pans (greased and floured) in 375° oven for 15 minutes, then in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: all good pie
directions: Beat the egg whites until they are stiff and fold in last to the pie mixture.
Bake in unbaked pie shell, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shane's triple forte fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in double boiler.
Add cocoa, powdered sugar and vanilla.
If too stiff, add some evaporated milk.
Add nuts. Pour into pan.

title: jello-pretzel salad(dessert)
directions: Crush pretzels.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Press pretzel mix into butter.
Bake at 325° for 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: kahlua
directions: Pour boiling water over
coffee grounds.
Add a dash of baking powder.
Let
stand 45 minutes, stirring often.
Strain coffee through double cheesecloth or jelly bag.
Add sugar and boil another 20	minutes.
Let
stand
until
completely cool. Add vanilla and Everclear.
Bottle
or	jar.
Time of preparation: 2 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Pour instant rice into 2-quart pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over rice.
Top with broccoli, then with chicken.
Mix soup and water. Pour over ingredients in pan.
Pour broth over this mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients (sugar, shortening, egg and salt). Add potatoes.
Sprinkle yeast into water and let stand 5 minutes. Add first mixture to yeast and water.
Knead in flour until mixture is stiff enough to handle.
Cover and let stand 2 hours.
Knead again and roll into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 450° until lightly brown.

title: spanish tomato rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Pour off half of the bacon fat; in remaining hot fat cook onion and green pepper until tender but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve with bacon crumbled on the top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade tomato sauce
directions: Cut tomatoes into large chunks; put in kettle.
Cook 15 to 30 minutes until tomatoes are soft, stirring constantly.
Fill blender 3/4 full with cooked tomatoes.
Cover blender.
Blend at high speed until tomatoes are very juicy.
Then into large bowl, press tomatoes through coarse sieve, discard seeds and skin. Return sieved tomatoes to same pot.
Put in crushed garlic and add remaining food ingredients.
Over high heat, heat tomato mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, 4 hours or until sauce reaches consistency, stirring occasionally.
Put in processed jars.
Process boiling water bath 10 minutes for pints, 15 minutes for quarts.
Makes 10 pints or 5 quarts.

title: civil war tea cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, soda and salt.
Cream mixture with butter; add egg and mix well.
To this, add the water, vinegar and vanilla.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Cover bottom of round casserole dish with 2 or 3 Tbsp. enchilada sauce.
Place a tortilla over the sauce.
Spread on a thin layer of refried beans.
Follow with a layer of grated cheese and a layer of green peppers.
Add another tortilla and cover it with enchilada sauce.
Add the hamburger, then the olives followed by the onion.
Top with another tortilla.
Cover tortilla with enchilada sauce, then top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bisquick rolls
directions: Mix in order; knead 20 times.
Roll out.
Cut and place in pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the water.
Cook until water is all gone, chopping meat with the spatula as it cooks.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, then reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: coconut custard
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Mix in milk, flavoring, coconut and salt.
Pour in two pie shells and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all together well.

title: potato cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel potatoes and grate into bowl. Grate cheese and add to potatoes.
Beat in eggs, milk and seasoning.
Pour into ovenproof dish.
Bake for 40 minutes, until top is golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: stewed apples
directions: Peel, core, slice apples. Wash and slightly drain. Place in heavy saucepan. If apples seem dry, add 1 Tbsp. water; cover. Cook on moderately hot burner, stirring often. Stew until tender. Add sugar and butter. Cook over medium high heat until contents thicken. Pour into 1 1/2 qt. baking dish. Bake approx. 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Top with marshmallows; brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir together pineapple and pistachio pudding.
Add marshmallows, Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until served.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge roll
directions: Combine milk and cocoa in top of double boiler; blend, then add sweetener and salt.
Heat to boiling point, then add vanilla.
Pour this mixture over the cracker crumbs and mix; shape into two rolls. Roll in small amount of the graham cracker crumbs, reserved from original 3 cups or roll in flaked coconut.
Chill two hours or overnight, then slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Nuts and coconut can be added to fudge for variety.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour, then blend 3 well beaten egg yolks into dry ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Cook raisins and drain. Add raisins, pecans and sour cream to egg yolk mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: skin on potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes, leaving skin on.
Layer all ingredients in bowl.
Pour 1 jar Mazelle or other Ranch dressing over all ingredients.
Toss and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate butterscotch scotcheroos
directions: In large saucepan, cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Press in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt chips until smooth.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Mix with cold water into a soft dough.
Grease pan well.
Pour mixture into the pan and bake at 425° until the crust is brown.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Heat water and margarine until margarine melts. Remove from heat and add flour. Stir with a wooden spoon. After cooling, add eggs, beating one in at a time. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 400° for 25-30 minutes. Cool. Mix together pudding, cream cheese and milk. Spread on crust and cover with Cool Whip.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Mix dressing and seasoning in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly. Refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: muffins
directions: In a bowl pour boiling water over shortening and cereals.
In a separate bowl, mix together all other ingredients.
Add the cereal mix and mix well.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.
Store unused batter in refrigerator. This batter can be kept in fridge for a week or more.
It's fun to put some in a jar and take to a friend or a shut-in or someone recuperating from an illness.
Be sure to put baking instructions on a tag or card.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute celery in butter.
Mix with remaining ingredients except corn flakes and almonds.
Place in greased casserole dish. Top with corn flakes and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot apple spice sundae
directions: Melt oleo in a saucepan; stir in brown sugar, cinnamon and pie filling.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and stir in pecans. Serve warm over ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts and drain well on paper towel.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese.
Add chilies and artichoke hearts.
Mix well.

title: cherry cooler
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover; process until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: no crust egg custard
directions: Mix first
ingredients.
Add canned milk.
Pour into well-greased and floured
pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oyster cocktail sauce
directions: Combine and mix well.

title: orange slush drink (julius)
directions: Do all in blender until frothy.

title: oven barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown 8 loin chops in a skillet, then place in a casserole. Season with salt and pepper.
Top each with a slice of lemon and onion.
Mix brown sugar and tomato sauce.
Pour over chops.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Mix together hamburg, egg, bread crumbs, onion and salt.
Roll into balls and brown.
Mix other ingredients and add to meat balls.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies and chocolate stars
directions: Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Add egg; blend.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to cream mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended. Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and depress top with spoon slightly.
Place chocolate star in center.
Press down slightly.
Bake 7 minutes or until golden brown at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and mix ingredients (except cheese) together and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese to top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed by box.
Then mix mushroom soup and tuna in with macaroni and cheese.
Put in a casserole dish and top with cheese of your choice.
Put in oven and cook until cheese is melted.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Shape into a ball and roll
in crushed nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers or sliced apples.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Core apples and slice into round 1/4-inch thick slices. Combine sugar, water, candies and food coloring; bring to a boil. Cook slices 10 minutes on each side in syrup.
Boil syrup down; cool.
Store in a covered container.
Can be kept for several weeks.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll into a ball and refrigerate.
Roll ball into crushed almonds after it chills. Quick and easy; best if made ahead.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma craun's homemade ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Add cream, milk and salt.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a hard ball.
Beat egg whites and mix.
Beat until it starts getting hard, then add pecans and flavoring.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Cool and allow to sit until firm.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Pour 1 can of tomato soup over top.
Bake 2 hours at 350°. Sprinkle with cheese the last 10 minutes (optional).

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and apples.
Cover with water and bring to boil and simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cream.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot syrup. Cover tightly and cook 20 minutes.
Do not lift lid.
Serve with cream.

title: garbanzo stuffed peppers
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, basil and parsley.
Reserve some cheese for topping on peppers, and add remaining cheese to mixture.
Fill peppers.

title: heavenly caramels(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart glass measuring cup with handle, combine sugar, heavy cream, corn syrup and butter.
Microwave at High for 5 minutes.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.
Microwave at High for 12 to 13 minutes or until mixture reaches 246°.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares and wrap individually in waxed paper.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: date balls
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, chopped dates and oleo. Bring to boil over med. heat stirring often.

Cook over low heat for 10 min. Mixture will begin to leave sides of pan, cool slightly. Add Krispies and nuts. Spread coconut on wax paper or foil. Drop by teaspoon onto coconut and roll into small balls, spread more coconut as needed.

title: sausage and sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage until brown, also onion.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into balls.
Dip in egg and milk mixture; roll in cracker crumbs.
Brown in oil.

title: almost orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or container; blend at high speed until frothy.
Serve immediately in tall glass.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
