Add eggs, 2 cups flour and milk alternately.
Take 1 cup flour, dates, pecans, coconut and candy slices.
Dredge all ingredients in the
cup of flour, then mix well with
the batter.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Cook broccoli.
Mix together the rice, broccoli, Cheez Whiz, celery and soup.
Mix well and place in casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Using a rolling pin, flatten each slice of bread.
Combine Blue cheese, cream cheese and egg in small bowl, mixing well. Spread evenly on bread, covering to edges.
Place 1 asparagus spear on each slice of bread; roll up.
Secure with 3 toothpicks. Dip in melted butter.
Place on a baking sheet and freeze.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa into a bowl.
Cream oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add food coloring.
Combine buttermilk and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add to oil, sugar mixture, alternate with dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon into two greased 9-inch round pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Combine milk and remaining sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Spoon evenly on each layer before frosting.

title: no knead bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Mix. Beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with cloth and let rise in a warm, draft-free place until doubled in size.
Grease muffin tin, cookie sheet or loaf pan.
Stir down dough.
Pour into loaf pan or fill muffin cups half full or shape into rolls.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size again.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes for rolls or muffins, slightly longer for loaves.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add one layer of cheese slices over hamburger mixture.
Cover with your favorite pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat together, on high, shortening, butter, sugar and brown sugar for about 5 minutes.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time mixing well after each egg.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.

title: hot green tomato pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and black pepper; heat to boiling.
Add tomatoes, onions and hot peppers to mixture; heat to boiling.
Remove; fill hot sterilized pint jars with vegetables and liquid, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal and process in a boiling water bath 15 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and membranes; wash.
Simmer peppers for 7 minutes in enough water to cover.
Let stand.
Brown beef.
Remove excess grease.
Return to heat and add green onions and seasoned salt.
Mix in rice.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of mixture into peppers.
Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook ground beef, onion, celery, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in kidney beans, undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, chili powder, salt, basil and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach salad with dressing
directions: Toast almonds in shallow pan at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Preparation time: baking time 45 minutes.
Make ahead 24 hours.

title: outrageous cheese cake
directions: Melt butter for graham cracker crumbs.
Mix and press into spring-form pan and 3/4 up the sides.
Put in freezer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Place chicken, celery, scallions, jalapeno pepper, red pepper, garlic and cheese in a mixing bowl and toss to combine.

title: custard ice cream
directions: Scald milk on medium high heat.
Beat eggs until yolks and whites are blended.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Slowly add milk while stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water on high heat. Cool and add whipping cream and vanilla.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.
Choice of toppings and garnishes are optional.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender. Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
In a large mixing bowl, combine soups and milk. Add to this mixture the vegetables and all other ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, covered, then an additional 5 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: garlic and herb chicken
directions: In microwave baking dish, mix together olive oil, tomato, celery, parsley flakes, garlic, salt, pepper, oregano, basil and nutmeg.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Add chicken, covering with mixture.
Cover; refrigerate overnight or for at least 3 hours.
When ready to cook, cover baking dish with wax paper; microwave on High for 10 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes.
If fork cannot be inserted in chicken with ease, return to microwave for brief additional cooking.
To serve, remove garlic slices and spoon sauce over chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in large baking dish.
Sprinkle on package Ritz crackers over top.
Pour 1 to 1 1/2 sticks melted margarine over top.
(I use a little less.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german meat balls
directions: Make ground beef into balls and mix lightly first 6 ingredients.
Brown slowly on all sides.
Add broth, mushrooms and onions.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: diabetic punch
directions: Mix orange juice and pineapple juice together.
Add 4 envelopes Sweet 'N Low, vanilla, almond flavoring and lemon juice.
Add more Sweet 'N Low to taste.
When ready to serve, add Sprite.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing.
Pour soup into baking dish.
Cut up chicken; put into soup.
Place stuffing on top of soup and chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: methodist fruit
directions: Mix it all together; serve.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix 2 packages of Jello with 2 cups of hot water, then add 1 1/4 cups cold water in a 3 quart dish or pan.
Add pineapple and a layer of bananas and sprinkle top with marshmallows.
Set in refrigerator until very firm.

title: caraway chicken
directions: Divide spinach into four au gratin baking dishes (microwave-proof if using microwave).
In a large skillet sprayed with nonstick coating, put chicken and cook over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender or no longer pink, turning pieces occasionally.
Put chicken on top of spinach.
Pour sauce over chicken; cover with foil, seal, label and freeze.
Serves 4.

title: sparkling champagne jelly
directions: Combine sugar and wine in 3-quart glass casserole.
Cover. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir once after 4 minutes.
Cook 1 minute after mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Stir in pectin.
Ladle into hot, sterilized glasses to within 1/2-inch of top.
Cover immediately with 1/8-inch layer of hot paraffin.
To insure a good seal, paraffin must touch all sides of glass. Let stand until paraffin hardens.

title: macadamia chocolate chip cookie
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and dry ingredients, then add chips and nuts.
Roll in log.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, then slice.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes in ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat butter, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine cheese and margarine in a large bowl.
Mix well. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Gradually add flour mixture to cheese mixture, mixing until dough is no longer crumbly.
Shape into a ball.
Roll 1/3-inch thick.
Use a pastry wheel or knife to cut dough into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour squash(serves 8)
directions: Cut zucchini, yellow squash and celery into thin slices. Place in large, shallow bowl.
Stir in onion; set mixture aside. Combine and heat together in saucepan corn oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar.
Heat to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar. Pour sauce over vegetables at once.
Cover and chill 4 hours. Drain and serve.
Contains approximately 190 calories per serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; cool. Combine cocoa,

sugar, cornstarch and salt in a medium saucepan. Beat egg yolks. Add small amount of milk; blend until smooth. Pour over remaining milk. Cook and stir until mixture boils; boil and stir until thick, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla. Pour in pie shell. Beat egg whites; add 2 tablespoons sugar per egg white. Put on top and brown.

title: mom roles' raisin cake
directions: Bake in greased loaf pans for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Cook cake in sheet pan as directed.
When done, punch holes in top with toothpick.
Heat the pineapple and sugar in saucepan just to dissolve sugar.
Pour over warm cake.
Cook the vanilla pudding as directed and pour over cake.
Then spread 1/2 package coconut over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Spread remaining 1/2 package coconut.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Spread oyster crackers in single layer on a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crackers. Stir very well.
Bake at 150° to 200° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes until brown.

title: louisiana crabmeat au gratin(great dip!)
directions: In a large skillet make a white sauce with the butter, flour and milk.
Add the bouillon and egg.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add the wine, Tabasco, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Add the crabmeat to the sauce and pour it into a 1 1/2-quart casserole or 6 ramekins.
Sprinkle the mixture with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Let chill in refrigerator overnight for spices to set in, then reheat.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Turn vegetables into saucepan.
Add onion, flour, salad herbs, salt and black pepper.
Mix until vegetables are coated with the flour.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Just before serving, blend in the Cheddar cheese and cream cheese, if used. Taste the soup and add mustard as desired.
Serve immediately.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve chilled.

title: carol's chili
directions: Lightly brown chili meat.
Drain.
Add to 3 cups boiling water. Add remaining ingredients as listed.
Cook for approximately 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
If needed, add masa for thickening to your desirability.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Stir 1 to 2 heaping tablespoons into 1 cup of hot water.

title: big red salad
directions: Set Jell-O and water slightly.
Mix in pineapple and whole cranberry sauce mix and set.

title: tapenade(poor man's caviar)
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients together except oil.
Add oil, a little at a time, to produce a firm, spreadable mixture.
Serve at room temperature in a small bowl, crock or souffle dish. Excellent with a hearty loaf or Melba toast.

title: health salad-romania(salata sanatatea)
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers and apples. Wash, peel, and grate the carrots. Wash lettuce and tear into small pieces. Mix all vegetables with salt, lemon juice, and oil. Place in salad bowl and decorate with tomato slices. Serve

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops of peppers off and remove seeds.
Mince onions and brown in Crisco.
Mix into meat, rice and seasonings.
Stuff peppers to 1/4 inch from top.
Place upright in roaster; add the tomato juice.
Make sure peppers stay upright.

title: codfish casserole
directions: Let cold water run over fish for 15 minutes.
Cover with cold water and heat slowly to boiling, but do not boil.
Drain and repeat process once more.
Combine fish and remaining ingredients except buttered crumbs.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in pan of hot water at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with egg sauce.
Serves 5.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas and apples.
When ready to serve, add bananas and apples.

title: shoe string chicken salad
directions: Mix and moisten with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Just before serving, add 1 1/2 cups shoe string potatoes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread dough (let rise) overnight in refrigerator. Butter long cake pan.
Chop walnuts and put in cake pan.
Pinch walnut size pieces of dough and let them touch- put in single layer.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Melt butter, sugar, pudding and milk.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Pour over dough and let rise 2 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
After baking, immediately flip onto a cookie sheet.

title: blue cheese biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters. Arrange in two 8-inch round pans. Melt butter and cheese.
Pour mixture over biscuit pieces.
Cover all biscuits well with mixture.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes or until golden brown. Take out and break apart and serve.
Makes 40. Great for a meeting or brunch.

title: western style stew
directions: Saute onions, peppers and celery in shortening. Add meat and salt. Brown meat on all sides, stirring frequently. Add tomato sauce, bay leaf, green chilies and water. Simmer 3 to 4 hours. Add potatoes, turnip and carrots. Thicken to desired consistency with flour and water paste. Simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Put cherries in, then pineapple.
Put cake mix and pecans in. Pour butter in.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash shrimp and set aside.
In a medium skillet, melt butter.
Add oil, parsley, garlic, salt, tarragon and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Remove skillet from heat.
Add shrimp, tossing to coat with butter mixture.
Pour into a shallow baking pan, arranging shrimp in a single layer.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: shower punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: tomato cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter generously a 9-inch ovenproof glass pie pan.
Line the pan with the bread, buttered side down. Slice tops from tomatoes and place on bread.
Sprinkle tomatoes with salt, pepper, sugar and grated onion.
Cover with grated cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir undiluted soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion until blended.
Stir in broccoli and cheese. Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add bananas, nuts and all dry ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers and chopped fine almonds on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Use 3-quart casserole dish.
Serves 16.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Makes 1 pie.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned on top, around 30 minutes, or when firm in the middle.

title: mango sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients and toss gently to mix. Taste and adjust seasonings.
Serve within 1 hour.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: mama's lemon sponge
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice, egg yolks and milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in pan of water (1 inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Good after a heavy meal!

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour over dry stuffing mix.
Pour half of stuffing in casserole dish.
Place boned chicken on stuffing.
Put remaining stuffing on top of chicken.
Mix the 2 cans of soup with 2 cans of chicken broth and pour over top of stuffing.
Bake in oven until well heated and bubbly all over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Blend in flour and salt. Force through Spritz gun or cookie press onto cookie sheets. Decorate with bits of cherries.
Bake in hot oven (375°) for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.
Dough can be made ahead and frozen.

title: worm hole
directions: Stir pudding and cookie crumbs together, then knaw down!

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets or use canned.
Peel and slice thinly.
Fry bacon slowly.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Crumble. Saute onions in bacon fat until golden brown.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir potatoes and crumbled bits of bacon in carefully.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand until ready to serve.
Yields 2 generous servings.

title: rumbledethumps (as in the scottish lion inn)
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cover with water and add salt.
Bring to a boil; simmer 15 minutes and drain.
In another saucepan, cover cabbage with water and add salt.
Cover and bring to a boil; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mash potatoes in a large bowl.
To potatoes, add cabbage and remaining ingredients.
Place in a baking dish and top with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country vegetable soup
directions: "Put it in grease and cook it for about an hour.
Take it out then eat it."

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread and crumble in a large bowl.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Mix bell pepper, pickle juice, pickles, onion and mayonnaise and let stand for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Cook bacon and crumble over all.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in tightly sealed jar.
Put 1 1/2 tablespoons of mix in a cup.
Add boiling water.
Add lemon, if desired.

title: baked pear pancake
directions: Peel and core pears; slice.
In large oven proof frying pan melt 1 Tbsp. butter over medium heat.
Add pears; sprinkle with suger.
Cook until tender and golden brown (about 10 minutes). Remove all pears and juice; wipe pan clean.
Add 2 Tbsp. butter to pan and melt.
Beat eggs, milk, flour, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon until almost smooth; leave some lumps.
When butter is hot pour batter into pan.
Arrange pears in center of batter and any juice.
Bake at 425° until puffed and golden brown (15-20 minutes).
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Note:
293 calories and 14 grams fat.
Serves 4.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients for about 20 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and Velveeta.
Can put in crock-pot and it will be ready in about 1 hour.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello and water; add 7-Up.
Fold in marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix butter, flour, egg, sugar and pineapple juice (cook until thick).
Let cool.
Fold in jello; put cheese on top.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat eggs; pour
pecans
in
bowl and mix with eggs and coat well.
Pour
sugar,
cinnamon and nutmeg over pecans; mix well. Pour out
on
buttered
sheet, then pour more sugar and cinnamon over top.
Cook
at
350° for 10 to 15 minutes, turning.
Let cool.
Great for gift.

title: bean and pea salad
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Mix all other ingredients; heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand at least 3 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Cook over low heat and serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake in a long, flat pan at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbly like meal.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: joanne's peanut brittle
directions: Sift together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe container sprayed with Pam.
Cook 8 minutes on High, stirring after 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir quickly until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto Pam-sprayed baking sheet. Spread to 1/4-inch thickness.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: holly wreath cookies
directions: In heavy pan, melt Parkay.
Add marshmallows and cook until melted on low heat.
Add vanilla and food coloring and mix well. Add corn flakes.
Mix well and drop by spoon on cookie sheets. Drop red hots on while still warm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Place in a bowl. Save juice from pineapple.
Put in saucepan.
Mix eggs, sugar and flour with juice.
Bring liquid to a boil and boil just until thickens.
Cool.
Prepare macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Cool and put in bowl with fruit.
Add liquid, marshmallows and Cool Whip. Blend together.
Will keep in refrigerator for 7 to 10 days.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix
cream
cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce and spread on slices of ham. Roll ham into roll. Chill and cut into 1/2 inch rolls. Serve on platter.

title: salsa mac
directions: Brown meat and drain. Stir in salsa and water. Bring to boil. Stir in macaroni. Reduce to medium, simmer 10-12 minutes until macaroni is tender. Add cubed cheese and melt.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder, salt and sugar; sift again.
Cut soft butter into dry ingredients as for pastry.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Spread in greased shallow pan (8 x 12-inch).
Press apple slices on top and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mom's raisin pie
directions: Boil the raisins in the water for 5 minutes. Put the brown sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Mix all together and pour over cooked raisin mixture. Add the lemon juice or vinegar.
Let cool. Put in pie crust.
Put top crust on. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil together margarine and cocoa; remove from heat and add sugar, flour, soda, salt and sour cream.
Add eggs last.
Bake on large cookie sheet at 350° for 22 minutes.
Cool.
Top with a large jar of marshmallow cream.

title: sour cherry salad
directions: Combine cherries, juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add cherry jello and dissolved Knox gelatine.
Let cool.
Add mandarin oranges and orange juice concentrate, pineapple and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yields 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Mix and roll or drop in 1-inch balls.
Put in miniature cupcake pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
After baking, press Peanut Butter Cup into center of cookie.
Press down sot op is even with cookie.
Dump from pan.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a food processor and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Great served with bagel chips, pita chips or breadsticks.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine onions, salt, pepper, crumbs, paprika, nutmeg and milk.
Add this mixture along with the eggs to the meat.
Mix well and shape into small meatballs.
Brown them in the margarine in a skillet.
Remove meatballs from skillet.
Add consomme to the drippings, then the water and cornstarch mixture to thicken.
Add sour cream and heat.
Add meatballs and heat gently.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy baked eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: double-boiler frosting
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in double boiler. Beat with mixer until mixture stands in stiff peaks, about 7 minutes.
Scrape sides of pan occasionally. Remove from heat. Fold in vanilla. Makes enough frosting for 2 layers or oblong cake.

title: con queso
directions: In saucepan, combine cheese, tomatoes and optional ingredients.
Melt over low heat, stirring constantly.
Use as dip or sauce.

title: okra with tomato sauce(4 servings)
directions: Heat the oil and saute the onion until soft.
Add the garlic; cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in the coriander.
Add the okra and stir until coated.
Cook the okra for 2 minutes.
Stir in the tomato paste.
Add the tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, then add the water.
Return to a boil; cover, reduce the heat and simmer gently for 45 to 50 minutes, checking that there is sufficient water.
Add the lemon juice and cook for 10 minutes more or until the okra is tender.
Serve.

title: thumb cookies
directions: Cream vanilla and lemon extract into the fat; add sugar gradually.
Beat eggs into the mixture thoroughly.
Put flour in all at once.
Stir to a thick dough.
Shape the dough into small balls, using about 1 teaspoon of the mixture each time. Put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a dent in each ball with your floured thumb.
Place a small amount of raspberry jam in each dent.
Bake cookies about 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: skillet medley
directions: In a skillet, partly cook hamburger.
If greasy, pour off grease.
Wash and dry okra before cutting.
Cut up the vegetables and add to the hamburger.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until vegetables are done, as you like.
Enjoy.

title: creamy shrimp dip
directions: Place cream cheese in 1-quart glass measure.
Cook in microwave 1 minute until soft.
Mix well.
Place soup in 2-cup glass measure. Cook in microwave until heated throughout, about 3 to 4 minutes. Add soup, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce to cream cheese. Stir well.
Serve hot or cold.
If serving hot, you may want to cook dip 25 or 30 seconds longer.

title: santa fe chicken tortellini casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 3-quart casserole.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook broccoli, onion and bell pepper in oil about 3 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables from skillet.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a greased casserole, layer the ground turkey, onions or if you use the onion soup mix, mix into ground turkey.
Then a layer of cheese and Tater Tots.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over top. Do not dilute soup with milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture will become the consistency of a cake batter.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
You may double the recipe.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add the Sweet 'N Low brown sugar, salt and vanilla gradually, while beating constantly.
Fold in nuts.
Arrange by teaspoon on a buttered and floured cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Makes 24.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine well chilled juices. Pour over ice in large bowl. Garnish with lime slices.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops lightly.
Roll in flour.
Brown in small amount of butter or Crisco oil.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Cook in oven until tender.
Remove foil.
Dilute one can of cream of mushroom soup.
Add green peppers and onions, chopped. Return to oven uncovered and simmer 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange sherbet jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add orange sherbet and crushed pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Add Cool Whip and nut meats (if desired).
Refrigerate until set.
You can use sugar less jello, no sugar pineapple and low calorie Cool Whip for low calorie dessert.

title: fried chicken
directions: Soak the chicken pieces in salted cold water overnight if possible.
Change the water several times.
You may use ice to help cool the water.
Drain the chicken.
Salt and roll in flour.
Use a cast-iron skillet with lid.
Use either solid or liquid Crisco or Wesson, or any good brand.
Cook chicken on a medium hot fire, turning often to brown evenly.
It is important to use the lid on your skillet.

title: chocolate-cherry cake
directions: Combine and mix by hand to keep cherries whole.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost while hot.

title: buttermilk drop doughnut
directions: Heat oil (2 to 3 inches) in a Dutch oven to 375°.
Mix flour, 1/4 cup sugar, the salt, baking powder, nutmeg and baking soda in a large bowl.
Add oil, buttermilk and egg; beat with a fork until smooth.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls (do not make too large or they will not cook through) into hot oil.
Fry about 3 minutes or until golden brown on both sides; drain on paper towels.
Immediately roll in sugar.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen drop doughnuts.

title: party rye
directions: Mix cheese, olives and onions with mayonnaise.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until the cheese bubbles.
Serve hot.

title: roast beef
directions: Put all ingredients in a deep baking dish and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Place in a greased casserole.
Over the top, pour tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 400°. Serves 5.

title: fresh cucumber pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, turmeric and celery seed.

title: beef grilled in la-lot leaves(bo goi la-lot)
directions: You will also need 5 (8-inch) bamboo skewers.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Store in refrigerator for several hours.
Form dough into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press with the bottom of a glass after dipping into granulated sugar.
Repeat before pressing each ball.
Bake about 5 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Stir cornmeal thoroughly into flour mixture.
Combine well beaten eggs, milk and shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well; pour into greased pan and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter; mix in egg and flavoring.
Blend dry ingredients in.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°; divide dough in half and roll out on lightly floured pastry cloth to 3/16-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake
7 to
8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: quick and easy quiche
directions: Sprinkle cooked meat over bottom of pie plate. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and onion. Combine milk, bisquick, eggs and Mrs. Dash. Beat for 1 minute. Pour over meat, cheese and onion. Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in a large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients except mozzarella cheese.
Place 1/2 the noodles in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Spread with half the cottage cheese filling, half the mozzarela cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat layer. Bake at 375 F for about 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each.
Add soda and flour mixture alternately with buttermilk. Then fold in orange slices, dates, coconut and nuts.

title: caramel pies
directions: Melt margarine;
add coconut, pecans and lightly brown in oven.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk in mixes bowl. Beat until smooth.
Fold in cool whip.
Put 1/4 cream cheese mixture into pie shell and sprinkle with 1/4 of coconut mixture. Drizzle with caramel topping.
Repeat layers, Refrigerate.
Can be frozen and served slightly frozen.

title: marshmallow crisp treats
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add marshmallows and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated with marshmallow mixture.
Press warm mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: meat balls
directions: Make into balls and brown in hot fat.
Add 1/2 cup hot water and simmer 20 minutes.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Put all ingredients in roaster in oven at 350° for 5 to 6 hours.
When done, break meat apart and put back in sauce.
Serve mixture on buns for chipped barbecued beef sandwiches.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch and water until thick.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add Jell-O and stir well until dissolved.
Add fresh strawberries.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Chill until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a large bowl, grate zucchini, onion and cheese (or run through food processor).
Crumble crackers with hands.
Add eggs and knead mixture.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt if desired. Transfer mixture into greased oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° until top is crispy golden (1 hour).

title: dirt and worms
directions: You will need 8 to 10 plastic cups.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix butter, flour and ground nuts.
Pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes; let cool.
Cream the cream cheese, vanilla, powdered sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip together.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk until thickened.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Chill.

title: classic belgian waffles
directions: With an electric or hand mixer, beat egg whites to a stiff peak.
Set egg whites aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, vanilla and butter to egg yolks and mix well.
Combine flour, salt and sugar and add to egg yolk mixture.
Mix until you have a thick, smooth batter.
Using a rubber spatula, fold egg whites into batter very gently.
A few small lumps are okay.
Do not overmix!
Cooks 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 waffles.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt caramels and marshmallows in microwave.
Add whipping cream and flavoring; mix well.
Slice apples and dip into dip. Eat good!!

title: hawaiian chicken breast
directions: Overnight, marinate chicken in soy sauce and sprinkle on Mrs. Dash lemon pepper.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar substitute.
Pour remaining soy sauce over chicken. Bake covered for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Uncover; add bell pepper and pineapple.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.
Each serving:
1 portion. Exchanges:
3 meat, 1/2 vegetable and 1 fruit.
Calories:

title: spanish zucchini
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add fresh diced tomatoes. Add spices and saute 15 minutes.
Add corn and zucchini.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups water to cover vegetables.
Simmer with covered lid for 35 minutes.

title: ground beef and green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Alternate layers of ground beef, potatoes, green beans and onion in baking dish until all ingredients are used, seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon tomato soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: lemon pepper chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Sprinkle the chicken breasts with lemon pepper seasoning.
Place in shallow baking pan that has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake until fork tender. This usually takes about 20 to 25 minutes. Remove the chicken from the pan and cut into bite-size pieces.
In a large bowl, combine the soups, sour cream, green peas, and chicken. Mix well.
Spoon into casserole dish. Combine the crackers, poppy seeds and melted butter. Mix well and sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake until bubbly. This will probably take about 25 minutes.

title: party burgers
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients; drain any fat.
Add the beef gravy and simmer 15 minutes.
Can be served over noodles or rice.
Meat can be made in patties and crumbled.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove bacon from pan.
Dice onion and cook in the bacon grease.
Add pork and beans, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard and brown sugar in with onions.
Crumble bacon in baked beans and let simmer.
Do not over stir or beans will be mushy.

title: sugar snowballs(easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Sift the rest of the ingredients, then mix together.
Roll into tiny balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.
Place some confectioners sugar in wax paper while warm.
Roll cookies in sugar.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add onions; cook until done.
Add cheese, garlic salt, oregano, paste and sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes. Place biscuits in a greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup mixture in cups.
Sprinkle with shredded mozzarella cheese.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 24 cups.

title: fruited bread pudding(4 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with no-stick cooking spray.
Combine first 4 ingredients in casserole; gently stir in remaining ingredients except yogurt. Bake on center oven rack 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with yogurt or milk, if desired.

title: chocolate pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly over crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator. Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown
meat
and
onion
in
Dutch oven and season with salt, garlic salt and paprika.
Boil noodles until just tender and drain.
Add noodles and the following ingredients:
corn, tomatoes and
soup.
Mix
together
and heat on top of stove. Put this in a large casserole dish and top with grated cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Very good.

title: pork chops and wild rice
directions: Season chops and brown in shortening.
Mix vegetables, seasonings and rice.
Turn into lightly buttered casserole. Arrange browned chops on rice mixture.
Combine soup and milk and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple and carrots.
In another bowl, mix the flour, soda, baking powder, nutmeg, salt, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: ham pie
directions: Chop ham, potatoes and carrots into small pieces.
Add ingredients to baking dish.
Add soup, peas and cheese.
Mix and bake at 350°
for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain green beans and peas.
Add onion, celery and peppers. Cover with sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and celery seed. Marinate in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time,
mixing well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla. Cook in a tube pan at 300 degrees for 2 hours.

title: date balls
directions: Boil together on low heat until dates are dissolved or melted, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool and add 2 cups Rice Krispies and nuts as desired.
Roll into balls.
Roll in nuts or coconut.

title: pork tenderloin picante(low-fat recipe; great flavor)
directions: You will need butcher's twine or toothpicks.

title: steak in pepper cream
directions: Place a 10-inch cast-iron skillet over medium heat until hot. Sprinkle salt in skillet.
Place steaks over salt.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove from skillet. Combine peppercorns, steak sauce and water in hot skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to loosen browned food particles on bottom of skillet.
Stir in whipping cream and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, 3 to 4 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add steak. Simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.
Yields 4 servings.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces, about 2 x 1-inch.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy pan and cook over low heat for about 15 to 20 minutes or put in microwavable bowl and cook in microwave on High for about 7 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients except cinnamon sugar.
Place by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle before baking with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dip pieces of meat in flour (which includes salt, pepper and paprika).
Place and brown in large roaster or skillet.
I use oil in pan to brown.
Add water to cover steak.
Add other ingredients (not necessary to stir) and cover with lid.
Bake in oven about 3 hours at 300° or until tender.
Makes its own gravy.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda to this.
Add M&M's.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Completely soften beans as directed.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir to combine.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours, on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: sweet and sour beets
directions: Mix
together and cook
until thick and clear. Add 2 Tbsp. butter and 2 Tbsp lemon juice.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir ingredients together and pour into casserole.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: crawfish delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and pour into a large, greased baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until rice is tender.

title: marla brown's fast and easy lasagna(easy)
directions: Boil the macaroni in water until cooked but still stiff. Drain.
In the lasagna baking pan, combine the Ricotta cheese, eggs, salt and pepper, grated Parmesan or Romano and seasoning and mix well.
Add and mix in the drained cooked macaroni and spread evenly in the baking dish.
Layer the Mozzarella over the macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle spaghetti sauce on top and add meat (if desired).
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Take out, cool a few minutes and serve.
If it is still very liquid, bake a few more minutes to set.
Can be frozen and reheated (covered).

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish.
Mix milk and soup together and pour over top of layers.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: west virginia stuffed peppers
directions: Crumble cornbread into large mixing bowl and add corn and tomatoes; mix until moist.
Add ham and mix thoroughly.
Stuff peppers with mixture from bowl.
Place one strip of bacon on top of each pepper.
Excess stuffing can be placed around peppers. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: greg's chili(chili cook off entry - 1994)
directions: Brown meat with onion; do not drain.
In blender, blend 1 can of chili beans.
Add this and rest of ingredients.
Stir frequently on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Let simmer for another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peppers and grits
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add green pepper, red sweet pepper and onion to drippings.
Cook about 2 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into bottom of crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: tulsa's own conners corner burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Cook well to medium-well.
Serve with no condiments.

title: betty's strawberry pie
directions: Fill baked pie shell with 1 quart of strawberries.
Cook Jell-O, cornstarch, sugar and hot water until thick and pour over strawberries.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Press half of this mixture into a greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with rhubarb or apples.
Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and vanilla until clear and thick.
Pour over fruit and top with the remaining crumbly mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail sugar cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Roll out thinly.
Cut in any shape.
Use cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° until lightly done.
Don't overcook.
These are easy to make and decorate for kids.

title: wild rice chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package instructions. Meanwhile, cook onion and celery in kettle until tender.
Stir in soup, sour cream, wine and curry powder.
Stir in chicken and cooked rice.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Stir before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating well on medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour 1/3 of batter into a greased and floured 9-inch round pan.
Stir spices, raisins and pecans into remaining batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Ice with filling, putting white layer in the middle.

title: the best brownies
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edge of pan.
Cool in pan.
Frost, if desired; cut into squares.
Makes 16.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Roll steak in flour, salt, pepper, dill weed and paprika. Brown in 1/4 stick butter in large skillet.
Add mushrooms, onion, garlic and bouillon.
Let simmer about 45 minutes.
Stir in sour cream (be sure not to boil).
Simmer a few minutes until heated and serve over hot noodles.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix dressing and pour over fruits, vegetable and chicken. Serve on lettuce bed.

title: yogurt fluff
directions: Dissolve sugar-free jello in boiling water.
Put in blender; blend about 1 minute.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 cup.
Add to jello and stir until ice is almost melted.
Blend in plain yogurt.
Chill and serve.
Makes 5 servings.
Try adding fruit, if desired.

title: cucumber rounds with smoked salmon mousse
directions: Cut each cucumber into approximately 20 rounds each.
Combine all remaining ingredients in mixing bowl of food processor. Process until smooth.
Chill for 1 hour.
Place mixture in pastry sleeve with leaf tip and pipe small amount on each cucumber round. If you don't have a pastry sleeve, just spoon a small amount on each cucumber round.

title: pecan pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with 1 cup chopped nuts and bake at 350° for an hour.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add egg yolk.
Sift flour and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture.
Spread into 10 x 15 cookie sheet.
Beat egg white slightly and spread over mixture.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: berry squirt
directions: Blend berries and yogurt at high speed in blender until smooth.
Stir in water.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: squash casserole #2
directions: Mix squash, onions, corn bread, butter, chicken soup, cheese, eggs and water chestnuts; place in casserole dish and bake at 350° until brown.

title: the recipe
directions: Mix and store in freezer.
Scoop out and add to Vernors or 7-Up.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add chilies, enchilada sauce and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix.
Put about 1/2 cup in bottom of a baking pan or casserole dish.
Layer shells (break the folded shells so there are two halves).
Put mixture over shells and then shredded cheese.
Another layer of shells, mixtures and end with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Fry in oil until brown on one side, turn over and fry on other side.

title: holiday cabbage roll
directions: Mix meat, rice, onion, pepper and soup.
Add spices.
Blanch cabbage leaves.
Place in boiling water for 4 minutes.
Place equal amount of meats in center of cabbage leaves.
Roll and fold ends of cabbage.
Place side by side in heavy pot greased with oil.
Pour soup over rolls and simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 30 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beat well after adding each egg. Crush vanilla wafers and add alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sunshine squares
directions: Combine the yellow cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick melted butter. Mix well; press this mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together the cream cheese, eggs and all ingredients, but 1/2 of powdered sugar.
Pour this mixture over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.
While still warm, sprinkle the cake with remaining powdered sugar.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Chill liquid ingredients.
Blend juices; add ginger ale and sherbet, stirring until sherbet is softened and partially dissolved.
Makes 40 servings.

title: egg dish
directions: *Add any or all of these.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown first four ingredients in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 400° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bake in covered dish or cover with Reynolds Wrap. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: beef roast in crock-pot
directions: Cut beef roast in large chunks.
Toss with flour.
Place carrot sticks in bottom of crock-pot.
Place meat on top of carrots in layers with one envelope soup mix sprinkled between layer.
Add 1 can tomato soup and 1/2 cup water.
Cook on low all day until tender.

title: orange zucchini cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in cereal, peel and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch glass baking dish or double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes for small pan, longer for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Spread with frosting.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and 1/2 of onion; set aside.
Mix together cornmeal, milk, eggs, oil, soda, salt, corn and remaining onion.
Grease deep baking dish (I use black iron pot).
Pour half of cornbread mixture, layer with meat and sprinkle with jalapenos and half of cheese.
Pour remaining cornbread over top and cover with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for about 1 hour.

title: german sausage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes.
Mix Cheez Whiz with sour cream.
Layer sliced potatoes and sausage.
Pour Cheez Whiz mixture over sausage and bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: turkey treats for dogs
directions: Cut each hot dog up into 12 to 15 slices.
Place single layer on paper plate.
Microwave on High about 7 minutes (the hot dogs will shrink and shrivel up).
Cool and freeze in plastic sandwich bags.
Excellent to take on picnics, to dog shows or on hikes. Take some "extras".
If you get hungry, they're very tasty.

title: sauerkraut salad(old german recipe)
directions: Combine sugar and oil; mix well.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Chill at least overnight.
Keeps well.

title: chocolate graham cracker crust
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Press evenly on bottom and sides of 9 inch pie pan.
Back at 375 degrees for 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots and raisins in a large bowl. Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar, salt, milk and lemon juice. Toss with carrots and raisins. Chill well before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: beef porcupines(meatballs)
directions: Combine beef, Rice a Roni and egg.
Mix well.
Form beef mixture into Meatballs.
Brown in skillet.
Combine seasoning packet with 3 Cups of hot water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Thicken Gravy if desired. Make a day or two ahead - great for busy days!

title: vera mae's peach salad
directions: Heat pineapple until hot, stirring constantly, but do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Mix well in dry Jell-O; add buttermilk. Mix well. Chill until set.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, peppers, and onions in salt and water (enough water to cover) for 2 hours and drain.
Rinse well.
Make a syrup of vinegar, brown sugar, turmeric, and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil. Pack cucumber mixture into hot jars and pour syrup over cucumbers.

title: japanese fried rice
directions: Chop bacon fine and fry until crisp in a heavy skillet.
Add green onions (save some green tops).
Add celery and green pepper. Stir until somewhat soft.
Stir this mixture with rice, adding soy sauce, salt, pepper and Accent to taste.
After well stirred, add mushrooms (drained) and green onion tops.
Serves 8.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, crackers, salt, pepper, garlic, onion, and 1/2 - 3/4 cup milk in a large mixing bowl.
Mixture should be moist and sticky.
Shape into desired size meatballs/patties and brown.
Mix soups and 1 1/2 - 1 3/4 cup milk and pour over meat.
Simmer about 30 minutes or until meat is cooked and gravy is thick (more milk can be added if gravy is too thick).

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple and mix thoroughly. Arrange pineapple rings in well-greased loaf pan.
Spoon ham mixture over pineapple and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: delaware strawberry supreme surprise
directions: Mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: cheesy corn bread *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cream 1/2 cup butter with sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in corn and cheeses. Sift together dry ingredients and add to corn mixture; blend well. Pour batter in pan; put in oven and reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake bread until golden brown and begins to pull away from sides of pan, about 55 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Spoon flour into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour measured flour onto wax paper.
Add salt to flour and stir to blend.
Bring shortening and water to a boil in saucepan.
Add blended dry ingredients quickly.
Beat constantly until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove mixture from heat and let stand until cool.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Fill with favorite filling when cool.
Top with Hot Fudge Sauce.

title: french onion soup
directions: You will need a crock-pot for this recipe.

title: coconut cake supreme
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions, using 8-inch pans.
Split layers when cooled.
Stir together sugar sour cream and coconut.
Take out 1/2 of the mixture and set aside.
Put remaining half of mixture between the layers and stacking until all are used up.
Add cool whip to mixture set aside and frost cake. Can be stored up to 3 days in refrigerator or eaten the same day.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients and spread over chicken wings.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into thick slices.
Cover with water.
Salt to taste.
Boil until tender-crisp.
Drain, saving 2 cups liquid.

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with salt.
Saute steak in oil in skillet until brown.
Add pepper and onion wedges.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Add mixture of cornstarch, mustard, broth and water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lo-cal jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Drop in frozen strawberries and stir in pineapple.
Put 1/2 of jello mixture in a large rectangle dish.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours or until firm. Allow other 1/2 to remain at room temperature.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended.
Spread mixture on firm jello and pour remaining 1/2 of jello on top.
Chill.

title: ham-ball stew
directions: In large bowl pour milk over cracker crumbs.
Add meat, salt, pepper, mustard, chives and eggs; mix lightly.
Shape in 24 balls. In Dutch oven or large, deep skillet, mix wine, water and bouillon; bring just to boil.
Add meatballs.
Cover and simmer (do not boil) about 50 minutes or until meatballs are cooked.
Remove to warm serving dish.
Stir blended flour into pan liquid, cook and stir until thickened.
Pour over meatballs.
Sprinkle with dill weed. Serve over warm rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt; set aside.
In small pan, cook oleo, cocoa and water over low heat; bring to a boil.
In small bowl, combine milk, eggs, vinegar, baking powder and vanilla. Beat until eggs are mixed in.
Pour all ingredients together in large bowl (with sugar and flour).
Mix well.
Pour into cookie sheet with 1 1/2 inch sides.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 475°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix together with mixer until smooth.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix peanut butter and margarine.
Ad powdered sugar, then Rice Krispies.
Form small balls.
Melt in double boiler, chocolate chips, wax and Hershey bar.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.

title: mamma coon's peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir sugar and milk on stove until it begins to boil.
Add peanut butter and cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Let cool.
Add vanilla.
Beat until it is creamy and begins to lose its shine.
Pour onto greased wax paper or into greased pan. Let set.
Cut into squares.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour, water, vanilla and pecans. Chill for 1 hour or until stiff.
Shape in fingers.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt shortening in large pot.
Add onions and celery; saute. Add meat; cook until browned.
Add all except beans.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours; stir.
Add beans for last hour of cooking.

title: fruit cake
directions: Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: coconut toast
directions: Melt margarine and spread on both sides of bread.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Beat together egg and sugar, spread on bread slices.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Bring to boil water, crumbled meat, onion, celery and spices. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add tomatoes, sauce and Veg-All; bring to boil. Cook 15 minutes.
Add orzo macaroni; cook 15 minutes.
Total time 1 hour.
Pot to use:
Minimum 4-quarts.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Heat in double boiler until cheese is melted.
Do not overheat.
Do not dilute with water.
Serve with breadsticks, celery or any fresh vegetable.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Add strawberries, pineapple, pecans and bananas. Jell half the mix.
When firm, add sour cream and rest of jello mix.
Chill until firm.

title: butterscotch nuggets
directions: Make balls, then flatten them.
Put a hole into the middle of the cookie, but not all the way through.
Melt chocolate chips. Stir in some icing sugar.
Drop that into hole and put half a nut on top.
Bake until golden brown.

title: iceberg cucumber pickle
directions: Slice cucumbers and mix with lime water; let stand for 24 hours.
(Best to use old churn or enamel canner; stir occasionally.)
Wash thoroughly and place in ice water for 3 hours. Rinse again.
Place cucumbers in enamel cooker.
Mix sugar and vinegar together and pour over cucumbers and let set overnight.
I put the spices in a cheesecloth bag and tie up so the spices won't be all through the pickles.
Let the spices soak in with the cucumbers, sugar and vinegar.

title: deer barbecue
directions: Boil deer roast until done.
Cut in small chunks.
Set aside. Brown hamburger, sausage and onion together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add one cup water, broth, ketchup and 3/4 bottle of sauce in large pot.
Add the chunks of roast.
Stir.
If it is not juicy enough, add more Maurice's sauce or broth.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: *chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Mix together sugar and corn syrup and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate and butterscotch morsels.
Spread over the top.
Let set until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Make Jell-O.
Allow to cool.
And add other ingredients.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan or mold.

title: weenie hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut hot dogs and bacon into sections.
Wrap bacon sections around hot dog sections and hold with a toothpick.
Place single layer in baking dish; sprinkle brown sugar over and add slices of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 - 30 minutes.

title: bologna salad
directions: Using a food processor or grinder, grind all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Use enough mayonnaise to make a good spread.

title: sweet barbecue sauce for ribs or chicken
directions: I never measure so taste as you go.

title: fried doves
directions: Clean and split doves.
Rinse, dry and roll in seasoned flour. Melt butter and oil in heavy skillet.
Put doves into hot fat and cover skillet for 5 minutes.
Remove cover and cook until tender.

title: butter almond classic cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat oleo with 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add extract.
Stir flour and gradually add to mixture. Add nuts and mix together until a dough forms.
Shape dough into a ball, seal in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Divide dough into 8 pieces.
Lightly flour hands and work surface.
Shape each piece into a 1/2 inch thick roll. Cut each roll into 2 inch pieces.
Arrange on ungreased cookie sheets and shape each into a crescent, tapering the ends by gently pinching them.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until very light brown. Cool cookies; dust with sifted remaining sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: sunday morning omelet
directions: Spray nonstick omelet pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Beat eggs with water until mixed.
Pour into pan.
Apply low heat.
Put cover on pan.
When omelet is firm, put ham, olives, salsa and 2/3 the cheese on 1/2 of the omelet and fold over.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of folded omelet.
Cover pan until cheese has melted.
Place omelet on plate and garnish with sour cream.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crush Oreos into crumbs.
Melt butter and stir into crumbs. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust and chill 20 minutes.
Prepare pudding with milk and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding and chill at least 2 hours.

title: shrimp puppies
directions: Mix, drop into hot oil and fry.
Very, very good.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in an unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° until silver knife comes clean when inserted in middle.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Place Twinkies, cut lengthwise in half, in a 9 x 13-inch dish, side by side.
Spread crushed pineapple over Twinkies. Slice bananas and put over pineapple.
Mix pudding according to directions and spread over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator.
Let set for 6 hours.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in double boiler over hot water.
Slowly add sugar, milk and salt.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
This takes quite a while.
Slowly add condensed milk and stir well.
Cook as before for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Let stand until thickened.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
This keeps for a long time.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Note:
Need 2 dozen flat bottom ice cream cones.

title: erica's choice salad
directions: Wash and dry greens.
Place 1/3 of mixed greens in a bowl. Dot with 2 tablespoons mayonnaise and 1/3 of onion slices. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and dash of salt and pepper, 1/3 of the peas and 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat for 3 layers.
Do not toss.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Crumble the bacon.
Just before serving, top with bacon and toss.

title: puree cream of carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions.
Cook until soft. Add
rest
of
the ingredients except parsley and light cream. Simmer,
uncovered,
for
30 minutes.
Puree through a food mill or
blender.
Return soup to pan.
Add cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Garnish with parsley.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meant and onions together. Add rest of ingredients and simmer for about 1 hour. Serve with crackers or cheddar cheese and sour cream.

title: prune filling
directions: Cook all ingredients until tender. Blend in food processor until smooth.

title: brian's favorite chicken
directions: Dredge each chicken breasts in the seasoned flour. Shake off excess. Fry in olive oil until golden. Keep chicken warm in a 250° oven while preparing sauce.

title: spicy chicken with broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into 2-inch cubes.
Toss chicken in cornstarch, salt and white pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cut broccoli into flowerets and cook 1 minute in boiling water.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Cut green onions and chili into small pieces.
In hot wok or skillet, add 3 tablespoons oil, chili, soy, garlic, sugar and ginger root.
Stir 1 minute.
Add chicken and stir-fry until chicken is white.
Add broccoli and stir-fry until broccoli is hot.

title: mexican fiesta pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in chili powder.
Add cream cheese, chilies, olives and eggs; mix well.

title: pralines
directions: Place all ingredients, except pecans in a saucepan and stir. Bring

to a slow boil for 3 to 5 minutes stirring often until candy reaches soft ball stage. Remove from heat and beat until candy thickens but is still shiny. Add pecans and stir. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let stand until firm.

title: garlic bread
directions: Melt margarine and add garlic powder and oregano to taste. Brush on slices of bread.
Bake at 350° to warm through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Add 3/4 package stuffing and mix well.
Put chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Add rest of stuffing.
Pour 1 cup of broth over this. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, then broil for 5 minutes.

title: green dream
directions: Gently mix contents of pudding package.
Drain pineapple. Fold in pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Chill and serve.

title: cobweb cookies
directions: Beat together flour, sugar, vegetable oil, milk, vanilla, and eggs until smooth.
Pour batter into a plastic squeeze bottle with a narrow opening.
Heat a large (preferably non-stick) skillet over medium heat until hot; grease lightly.
Working quickly, squeeze batter to form 4 straight thin lines which intersect at a common center point to form a star shape.
To form cobweb, squeeze thin streams of batter to connect lines.
Cook 30 to 60 seconds or until bottom is golden brown.
Carefully turn.
Cook other side the same. Remove, cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: spinach and rice ring(otherwise known as green rice in our family)
directions: Mix well and bake 1 hour uncovered at 350°.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Melt chips and condensed milk in microwave on medium heat for about 2 minutes.
Remove; stir well and add vanilla, salt and nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Remove from refrigerator and cut into squares.
Store at room temperature loosely covered.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oven on broil, until brown all over.
Put in a Dutch oven with 5 cups water, onion soup and celery flakes.
Put in oven for 2 hours on 300°.
Take out of oven; add potatoes, carrots and celery flakes.
Put back in oven about 1 hour.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix shortening, orange juice and egg together.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Fold in cranberries and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheesy herb stuffed chicken
directions: Pound chicken to flatten and tenderize.
Divide cheese mixture between pieces of chicken.
Roll chicken jelly roll style.
In small bowl, combine parsley, bread crumbs and Parmesan.
Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in coating mixture.
Place chicken rolls, seam side down, in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cook sausage until crumbly.
Drain.
Combine meat and all other ingredients.
Save a little egg to brush on top of the 3 rolls before baking.
Each package will make 1 roll.
Pinch seams together to make a solid flat piece of dough.
Put 1/3 of meat mixture on each piece.
Spread evenly and roll.
Turn ends under. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes or until tops of rolls are brown.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together in order given. Refrigerate.

title: teriyaki london broil
directions: Pierce meat with fork (both sides) and place in a large food storage bag.
Mix teriyaki, wine and meat tenderizer in a small bowl.
Pour contents of mixture into the bag with the meat and allow it to marinate for 3 to 4 hours.
Cook on grill at medium heat while basting meat with marinade until desired tenderness.

title: pico de gallo(mexican hot salad)
directions: Wash vegetables real good.
In a medium bowl, chop all the vegetables.
Mix all together.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Let it chill for 1/2 hour in the refrigerator.
Enjoy with your meals!

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in long pan.
Cool. Pour cream of coconut and condensed milk over cake after punching many holes in cake with fork.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Easy.

title: mexican orange and lemon cookies
directions: Soak lemon or orange peel in 1 tablespoon of boiling water. Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and peel and water mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in flour alternately with juice.

title: corny corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in large bowl; add both corns, corn bread mix, sour cream and oleo.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and bake 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 side dish servings.

title: squash spectacular
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook squash in boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain well and mash.
Saute onions, bell pepper and water chestnuts in butter.
When tender, combine with squash.
Fold in cheese, mayonnaise, sugar, egg, salt and pepper. Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake 30 minutes.

title: pork egg rolls
directions: Mix soy sauce, sherry, 1 teaspoon of salt, sugar and pepper. Pour over pork.
Marinate, stirring occasionally 5 minutes.
Drain well and reserve marinade.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Mix altogether well.
Bake in muffin cups at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: lou's white fudge
directions: Melt butter and choc. in double boiler;
pour over cream cheese and add nuts.
Pour in buttered pan and cut when cool. Yummy!!!

title: new york cheesecake
directions: You will need a spring-form pan for this recipe.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook noodles and reserve 1/4 cup of this water.
Put hamburger in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in noodles, garlic to taste, soup, tomato paste and water.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: easy country style cream gravy
directions: Heat drippings in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour and cook until lightly browned.
Add your liquid.
Cook and stir constantly until smooth.
Will thicken as cooks.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease bottoms of 6 medium muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Beat egg, oil and buttermilk in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove muffins from pan immediately.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: chicken and mushrooms in wine sauce
directions: Skin chicken breasts and thighs and cut into serving pieces. Cook chicken in butter until no longer pink on the outside.
Add the sliced mushrooms and onions and brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over moderate heat for 45 minutes. Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on box. Put margarine and cheese in hot rice. Add rest of ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350° in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Add milk if too dry.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or until brown around the edges. Cool crust.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with spoon.
Do not beat.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, stir together flour and baking soda.
In larger bowl, beat margarine, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Salt and pepper or put in buttermilk for 1 hour then salt and pepper.
Then flour it and put in hot grease. Fry until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender in boiling water.
Drain and beat with a spoon until lightly mashed.
Melt the butter and pour over the dressing mix; combine well.
In a large bowl, mix the squash, carrot, onion, bell pepper, soup, sour cream and seasoning.
Add 1 cup of butter, dressing mix and 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart greased shallow baking dish.
Cover with remaining cheese and top with the remaining 1/2 cup of dressing mix.
Bake in a preheated oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine oats, both flours, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir to combine.
Stir in raisins and apples.
In a large bowl, combine egg, honey, oil and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix to form a smooth batter.
Drop batter onto ungreased baking sheet, using a rounded teaspoonful of batter for each cookie.
Drop 2 inches apart.
Dip fingers into water and press batter down to about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Bake until lightly golden, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Cook in a shallow pan on back of wood stove for about 30 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven until melted.
Remove.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce.
Add all cereals and nuts; mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven for 45 minutes; stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon-coconut surprise
directions: Add dry pie filling to sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Add pineapple in syrup and coconut.
Chill.

title: georgia peach pound cake
directions: Grease a 10 inch tube pan with 2 Tbsp. butter. Sprinkle pan with 1/4 c. sugar. Cream remaining butter; gradually add remaining sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla and mix well.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs and flavoring.
Add flour.
Spread on large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Cut through batter to make squares.
Spoon pie filling into each square.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until light brown. Batter puffs up around filling.
Recut squares when out of oven and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Fry chicken in butter with garlic and green pepper. Combine pimentos and mushroom soup.
Cook together 15 minutes and add chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth or stock until tender. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with meat mixture.
Serves 15 people.

title: tuna salad
directions: In mixing bowl combine all ingredients and mix well, but do not over mix.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Serve on sandwich with lettuce or on crackers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill for about 1 hour.

title: crab casserole
directions: Hard cook eggs.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, saute in butter, celery and onion until tender.
Remove from heat.
Into celery mixture flake crabmeat, milk, mayonnaise, olives, Worcestershire and 1 cup bread crumbs.
Remove shells from eggs and chop coarsely and stir into mixture until blended.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 6 large scallop shells or a Pyrex casserole dish.
Pour in mixture.
Add remaining crumbs in butter and sprinkle over crab mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly and golden.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 325 calories per serving.

title: seaside stew
directions: Brown mushrooms lightly in butter.
Add soup and cream, heat slowly until soup is thawed, blend in seafood and cheese. Heat, stir often.
Add
sardines	just
before serving.
Serve with hot butter rice or noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: seven-layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and spread the other ingredients in the order in which they appear.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: curried crabmeat, au gratin(a george rector recipe)
directions: Pick over crabmeat to remove any tiny bones or bits of shell. Dissolve curry powder in a little milk or cream and add to 1 cup hot white sauce.
Add crabmeat, mixing it gently, so as not to break the crab flakes.
Transfer the crabmeat to individual au gratin dishes (or scallop shells).

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend one egg at a time; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°. Drop small teaspoonfuls of dough into powdered sugar.
Roll in sugar; shape into balls.
