Place about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
These flatten to a "crinkle" while baking.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Grate carrots and mix well with other ingredients.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Pierce each squash once or twice with a fork and place in 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 1 or 2 minutes.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center of squash.
Set pulp aside, leaving squash shells in glass dish.
Place butter in a glass bowl. Microwave at High 30 seconds to melt.
Stir in squash pulp, salt, pepper, bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Fill squash shells with stuffing mixture.
Microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cream butter and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Stir in vanilla and melted chocolate.
Mix flour, soda and salt in bowl.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Fold in egg whites gently. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: granny's almost good for you cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix other ingredients except chips, raisins and nuts.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add chips, raisins and nuts; mix.
Drop by teaspoons on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until browned.
Yield:
5 dozen cookies.

title: robbie's good pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients.
Start in cold oven; turn to 325° and cook 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix together in bowl butter and powdered sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Blend together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture, blending well.
Add chopped nuts.
Roll dough out into two balls.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Flatten dough out and cut into 15 to 16 equal size pieces.
Shape into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While still warm, roll into powdered sugar.

title: chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: Dip meat in egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook meat on both sides until browned. Remove; pour off fat.
In same skillet, combine soup, milk and water; heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over meat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook milk, cornstarch, sugar, salt, egg yolks and vanilla in the top of double boiler or in microwave.
Cook until thick.

title: chicken philippine style
directions: Marinate chicken in mixture of other ingredients for about 30 minutes (or overnight).
This can be done in skillet to be used for cooking.
Heat on top of stove until it comes to a boil; cover and simmer for about 40 minutes or until almost all liquid is evaporated.
Serve hot or cold.

title: lemon filled angel food cake
directions: Bake cake and allow to cool.
Slice cake horizontally into four layers using serrated knife.
In a medium bowl, combine pie filling and yogurt.
Blend well.
Spread 1/3 of filling (1 cup) between each cake layer.
Frost top and sides with whipped topping.
Serves 12.

title: mom's persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan

title: maple acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut each squash in half lengthwise; remove all strings and seeds.
Place halves in large baking pan filled with 1/2-inch water.
Spoon 2 tablespoons syrup into each squash.
Sprinkle with pinch of nutmeg.
Cover and bake about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and place 1 tablespoon butter in each.

title: pot roast
directions: Pat roast dry and season with salt and pepper. In a Dutch oven, heat the vegetable oil over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking. Add the roast and brown on all sides, about 15 minutes. Transfer the roast to a plate and pour out all but 1 tablespoon of fat from the pan. Add the onions, carrots and celery to the pan and cook over moderate heat, stirring until golden. Place the roast back in the pan along with the bay leaves, thyme and enough of the beef stock to come up 2/3 of the way up the beef. Bring the pot roast to a simmer on top of the stove. Skim; cover tightly and set in the lower third of a 350° preheated oven. Regulate heat so that the liquid remains at a gentle simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until the beef is tender. Turn the roast over several times during its braising.

title: whiskey peppercorn sauce
directions: Saute shallots in drawn butter approximately 1 minute. Add garlic. Add whiskey to pan to deglaze.
Add au jus or chicken stock mixture, allowing the liquid to reduce to 1 1/2 quarts, approximately 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: 1-2-3 rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: better than sex chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil, water and vanilla. Blend well.
Add sour cream and beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube/Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: unbaked chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat to the boiling point and boil 2 minutes.
Stir constantly!
Cool. Stir in marshmallows and cracker crumbs.
Spread into a foil lined pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Melt the butterscotch chips and the peanut butter at low temperature on top of the stove.
Add the vanilla. Spread over the crumb mixture.
Let set to cold, then cut into bars.
This makes about 3 dozen.
A family favorite.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on jelly roll pan. Press to seal edges and seams together. Bake as directed on package. Cool. Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing. Spread on cooled crescent rolls. Put a light layer shredded Cheddar. Arrange vegetables including broccoli tops, cauliflower, sliced cherry tomatoes, black olives and mushrooms. Cut and serve.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Wash and cut the eggplant in half lengthwise.
Remove as much of the white portion as possible without breaking the shell.
Cut the pulp into small pieces and cook in small quantity of hot water for 10 minutes, or until tender.
Drain.
Mix together the melted butter and bread crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 of the crumb mixture for the topping.
To the remaining crumbs add the onion, beans, salt, pepper and the eggplant pulp.
Mix thoroughly.
Pile lightly
into the eggplant shells.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Pour a few tablespoons of hot water around the shells to keep them from sticking.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: veggie wedgies
directions: Lay crescent rolls out flat on 2 ungreased 12 x 18-inch cookie sheets.
Bake until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and dry Ranch dressing together and spread on cooled crescent rolls.
Top with any combination of 2 or 3 of the following finely chopped vegetables:
carrots, broccoli, cucumber, onion, green/red pepper, radishes, mushrooms, cauliflower, etc.

title: baby plum cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and spices together.
Add oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Mix in nuts and plum baby food.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken breast
directions: In square baking dish, layer bottom with chipped beef.
Wrap each chicken breast around a hunk of cheddar cheese.
Wrap a piece of bacon around the outside of each chicken breast,
Lay breasts on top of chipped beef.
Pour soup over chicken.
(Do not add water.)

title: baked boneless chicken breasts
directions: Place dried beef or ham in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam. Wrap breasts with raw bacon with ends on bottom of breast.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275° or until tender and lightly brown.
Bake, covered, half of the cooking time and uncovered until done. Serves 8.

title: my sister's salmon balls
directions: Drain salmon. Debone and pick out dark skin. Mash salmon and egg together and flour. Take 1/4 cup salmon juice and dissolve baking powder. Mix salmon juice with baking powder to salmon mix. Mix well. Into hot oil, drop by teaspoon heaping full. As they fry, they will turn over. When well brown, remove with a slotted spoon and drain well. Light and fluffy.

title: mushroom and cheese frittata
directions: Melt oleo in a 10-inch skillet.
Saute mushrooms and onion until golden.
Beat eggs.
Add to vegetables.
Let set.
Turn to low and cook until firm and set.
Place cheese on top.
Cook under broiler until bubbly and golden.
Cover skillet handle with foil. Slide onto plate.

title: easy fudge brownies(mixes in 5 minutes)
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup vegetable oil.
Add boiling water.
Stir until mixture thickens (about 1 minute).
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup oil. Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan or 2 (8-inch) square pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken rebecca
directions: Grease a 9 x 12 pan.
Separate dried beef and cover bottom of pan. Wrap chicken breasts wih bacon.
Place in over beef.
Mix cheese, sour cream and soup.
Spread over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with rice.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oleo together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar together and pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Cut long way first and then across.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Make a sauce by melting butter in saucepan; add flour.
When bubbling, gradually add the milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add grated cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Salt and pepper to taste; mix with the macaroni.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° until done.

title: pork chop and vegetable casserole
directions: In a large frying pan, add the shortening.
Brown the pork chops on each side.
Remove the fat from pan and place the thawed French-style string beans on top of the chops.
Peel and slice the potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on top.
Add 1/2 cup water, cover and cook until potatoes are done.

title: deluxe potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch or two 8 x 8-inch pans (bake one, freeze one).
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: sweet and sour pork (or chicken)(serves 4)
directions: Whisk together first 4 ingredients; add pork or chicken.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Remove pork from marinade; discard marinade. Dredge pork in 1/2 cup cornstarch.
Pour oil to a depth of 1/4-inch in heavy skillet or wok.
Fry in hot oil over medium heat 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and drain.
Reheat skillet with 2 tablespoons fresh peanut oil.
Stir-fry bell pepper and pineapple over high heat 2 minutes.
Add Seasoning Sauce.
Stir-fry until thick.
Stir in pork (chicken).
Cook 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: country steak and onion gravy
directions: Batter steak with flour, then brown in 1/2 cup oil on both sides.
Salt and pepper while cooking.
Put in large baking dish. Add balance of oil to pan.
Also, 4 tablespoons flour, stirring until brown.
In a bowl, pour can of onion soup.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cans water.
Pour into pan.
Stir until slightly thick.
Pour over steak in baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.
Gravy will thicken more while baking.

title: mock fruit pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and confectioners sugar and whip until smooth.
Spread on pound cake.
Top with sliced fruit.

title: tart shells
directions: Mix ingredients.
Divide into 6 equal balls.
Each ball will make 1 dozen shells.
Shape into large marbles.
Flatten into circles
and
press
into miniature muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes for unfilled shells.
If filled bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed except use only 1 cup milk.
Blend all cookies in blender or crush with rolling pin (filling included).
Remove small portion of cookies to sprinkle on top. Melt oleo and mix with cookies.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 Cool Whip with cream cheese.
Spread on cookie crumbs.
Spread pudding over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Then spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Chill and serve.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir again.
With wire whip, blend in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and milk.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Mix in pecans and pour into pie crust.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 50 minutes or until custard sets.
Serve cooled pie with Cool Whip.

title: soy chicken wings
directions: Heat all ingredients except chicken until butter and brown sugar are melted. Pour over chicken wings in deep rectangular dish.
Marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Cook at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain; serve warm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt on low heat, cream cheese, oleo and milk.
Add corn and green chilies and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over medium heat. Add pork and cooked turkey or chicken.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Add okra, onion and green pepper and cook for 5 minutes.
Add garlic, tomatoes, chicken broth, liquid from oysters, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes or longer. Add oysters or shrimp and cook for 1 minute.
Season to taste. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Heat milk and butter until it steams.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt; beat egg and vanilla.
Add to hot mixture.
Cook and stir constantly until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Stir with mixer.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans or 1 (12 cup) Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
The bread may be frosted, if desired, when cool.
(You may add up to 1 cup of apples, blueberries, strawberries, raisins and nuts or dried fruit to recipe.)

title: lucy's zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini squash in salted water and drain.
Mix all other ingredients.
Carefully stir in drained squash.
Pour into greased pan or dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and lower heat. Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Baste ribs every 15 to 20 minutes. This sauce is good with chicken.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
With blender, mix cream cheese, lemon juice and sugar.
After well blended, blend in cool whip.
Then pour or spoon into graham cracker crust.
Chill about 1 hour. Serve.

title: honey ginger napoleon topping
directions: In a chilled bowl, beat the cream until stiff.
Add honey, preserves and liqueur, mix gently, but well, after adding each ingredient.
Chill and serve as a topping for cake, ice cream or fresh fruit.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: barley soup
directions: Brown stew meat in oil.
Add water and cover.
Cook 1 hour. Add bouillon, tomatoes, carrots, onion, celery, barley, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large, ungreased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is a delicious way to use up leftover Thanksgiving turkey!

title: 7-up gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add the cream cheese, pecans, pineapple, and 7-UP.
Stir and chill until firm.

title: christmas strawberry nut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture into larger gelatin mold and put into refrigerator to set firm as quickly as possible.
(Keep other half out of refrigerator.)

title: lemon pie bars
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients well and then add dry mix.
Bake in 8-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Ice if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream milk and cheese until spreadable.
Add onions, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce and shrimp.
Good with Ritz crackers.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook the zucchini in 2 tsp. water for 6 minutes.
Add the crushed pineapple and cook 6 more minutes.
Add the lemon juice and remove from stove.
Add the jell-o and stir until dissolved. Pour into jars, put on lids, and keep in the refrigerator.

title: tiny pizza's
directions: Brown and drain sausage and hamburger.
Stir in velveeta. Pile on tiny bread slices.
Heat thru oven, can be frozen.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together. Place in skillet on low heat and add chopped dates. Cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until thick. Fold in pecans and Rice Krispies. When mixture has cooled slightly, with greased hands, form into small balls and roll in coconut. Refrigerate. Will keep well.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In large mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, butter, eggs and vanilla. Beat at low speed 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in nuts. Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until firm to the touch. Cool and cut. Makes about 2 dozen bars.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans well and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool.

title: freckled oatsies
directions: Combine honey, milk, oil and eggs.
Add flour, oats, bran, baking powder and salt.
Stir in raisins.
Mix.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Combine the corn and about a dozen saltine cracker crumbs.
Add the green pepper and milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole.
Roll 8 to 10 crackers into crumbs.
Melt the butter and stir in cracker crumbs; spread over top just before putting into oven.
Cook approximately 1 hour at 375° or until top is well browned.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add corn meal gradually to boiling water, stirring constantly. Let cool.
Add shortening, salt, egg yolks, milk and baking soda. Beat about 2 minutes and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into well oiled baking dish and bake in hot oven (435°) for about 40 minutes.
This is a delicious dish.
I could make a meal out of this by itself.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 2 cups water; set aside.
Mix boiling water, salt, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, yeast and 3 cups of flour; mix.
Add remaining flour until mixed.
Put in oiled bowl; let rise.
Punch down; let rise second time.
Punch down; shape into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown. Makes 2 dozen.

title: pickle sandwiches
directions: Drain pickles well.
Cut crust off bread.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Spread mixture on bread slices.
Roll drained pickles in bread.
Pinch edges of bread together to close. Place rolls, pinched side down, on wax paper.
Place in refrigerator overnight. When ready to serve, slice rolls crosswise into 1-inch slices and insert toothpicks.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all the juice from the canned fruit.
Save the pineapple juice.
Mix together the pineapple juice, Tang and vanilla pudding mix to make the sauce.
Fold in all the fruit except the bananas. Chill.
Put in bananas just before serving.

title: best apple butter
directions: Peel and core apples and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place in a large saucepan and pour cider over them.
Cover and cook 30 minutes over low heat or until the apples are soft.
Cool.
Puree apples in blender.
Put into a large baking dish; sprinkle with spices and stir well.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours or until it is deep brown and thick.
Cool and put in tight fitting jar. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Layer hash browns in dish.
Mix margarine, cream of chicken soup, Cheddar cheese, sour cream, salt and onion.
Spread on top of hash browns.
Top with corn flakes and remaining margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix together milk, honey, peanut butter and vanilla.
Roll in balls.
Roll in crumbs.
Place on pan to dry.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion and green pepper.
Cut celery on the slant and cook in water until crisp-tender.
Save broth.
Add hamburger mix to cooked rice, celery, mushroom soup and chicken-rice soup and soy sauce.
Cook 45 minutes in 350° oven. Top with Chinese noodles.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: spinach salad
directions: Put the last 7 ingredients in blender.
Mix well; pour over salad.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender to cornmeal size. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add with buttermilk to dry mix.
Mix well. Turn onto floured board and knead lightly. Roll out about 1/4-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush with butter. Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator and can be used as needed.

title: onion dip
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender. Let cool. Then blend onions and all other ingredients except chives. Add chives to the blended mixture and chill.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pitcher and put in freezer until ready to serve.
Keep in freezer when not serving.
This keeps it as slush.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let bread thaw and
rise to package directions.
Roll as flat as possible.
Top with butter, Mozzarella cheese and then thinly sliced pepperoni.
Roll up like jelly roll.

title: lasagna
directions: In separate skillets, brown hamburger and Italian sausage (best if removed from casing and crumbled while browning).
In another skillet saute chopped onion and mushrooms.
In large Dutch oven combine tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add hamburger, sausage, onion and mushrooms to sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Layer sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, Parmesan and shredded Mozzarella in lasagna pan until full.
Bake at 350° until cheese on top is melted and turning brown.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding fruit last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add milk and egg yolks and beat well.
Add shortening.
Mix.
Stir in beaten egg whites. Bake in hot waffle iron or griddle for pancakes.

title: saucy zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onions in small amount boiling water until tender. In saucepan, melt oleo; blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once; cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles. Combine with cooked vegetables. Place in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2 baking dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Stir in melted butter. After mix cools, stir in chocolate chips. Spray baking sheet with Pam. Put mix on sheet in tablespoon drops.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend with a fork.
Grease and 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: caribbean shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails on.
(If shrimp are frozen, do not thaw; peel under running cold water.)
Make a shallow cut lengthwise down back of each shrimp.
Wash out vein and pat dry. Heat oil (2 to 3-inches) in deep fryer or Dutch oven to 325°. Mix flour mixture (flour, salt and ginger).
Coat shrimp in flour mixture; dip into pina colada mix.
Pat coconut onto shrimp, covering completely.
Coconut adheres to shrimp if shrimp are fried immediately after being coated.
Fry the shrimp about 2 minutes, turning once, until coconut is browned. Dip in marmalade or cocktail sauce.

title: trash - puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together, blending well with wooden spoon.
Place Rice Chex in large bowl.
Slowly pour chocolate mixture over Chex and gently fold until completely covered with chocolate.
Take clean medium kitchen trash bag (that's how it got it's name).
Pour 1/2 box of sugar in it; then pour Chex mixture in and top with rest of sugar.
Close bag and gently roll bag from hand to hand.
Do this at least 10 times.
Open bag and each Chex will be individually coated.
To make trail mix, add peanuts and raisins after mixed.

title: old-fashion johnny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: heavenly cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from can of pineapple.
If necessary, add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling juice.

title: mystery cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat well and blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: dee's good soup
directions: Brown the beef.
Put everything undrained into large pan. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with cornbread.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift flour with spices.
Add flour mixture with sugar and shortening. Roll into balls size of walnuts.
Coat balls with sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.
Mix in large bowl the chocolate mixture, 1 cup flour, sugar, eggs and baking powder. Add the remaining cup of flour and nuts; mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours, then form into balls and coat with powdered sugar.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes (until firm to touch).

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put butter in skillet.
Melt; add sugar and dissolve.
Mix egg yolks and cornstarch; add cold milk, vanilla and salt in bowl. When well mixed, add to skillet and cook until thick.
Make meringue for top.

title: chili cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread batter according to pkg. directions and stir in chilies, cumin, oregano & sage.	Spread in greased 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20-25 min.
Cool.
In small bowl, combine mayo, sour cream and dressing mix; set aside.
Crumble half the cornbread into a 13x9x2 dish.
Layer with half of the beans, mayo mixture, corn, tomatoes, green pepper, onions, bacon and cheese.
Repeat layers cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Yield:
12 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter in square or oblong baking dish.
Combine corn flake crumbs, Parmesan cheese and dash of salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg, then in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn meat.
Bake 20 minutes more or until tender.

title: lime cream cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Bottom Layer:
Dissolve lime jello in boiling water; add pineapple juice.
Pour into oblong Pyrex dish.
When slightly jelled, add drained, crushed pineapple and return to refrigerator to congeal.

title: cabbage salad
directions: In a bowl, alternate layers of cabbage and onions.
Sprinkle sugar over cabbage and onions.
Set aside.

title: chuck steak pizzaiola
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from steak.
Place in a shallow glass baking dish with plenty of space around meat.
In a bowl, mix the rest of the ingredients.
Spread over steak.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes to one hour, until steak is tender.
Slice at an angle and serve with tomato sauce from pan.
This tastes great with roasted potatoes.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream the first two ingredients smooth on bottom of dish.
Add salsa or taco sauce.
If sauce used, use peppers.
Add tomatoes and cheese.
Use unsalted chips.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Stir.
Add melted butter or oleo, freshly squeezed lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Beat whole eggs well.
Add milk and salt; stir well.
Pour in pie crust. Bake at 425° for 3 minutes; then bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cook until firm when shaken or test with knife until it comes out clean.

title: tennessee chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in corn meal and salt.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Beat in lemon juice and peel.
Turn into shell.
Bake on lowest shelf of oven for 35 minutes until filling is golden brown.
Should not be firm.
Cool to room temperature.
This is like the filling of a pecan pie without the nuts.
Served 10 to 12.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife slips out clean.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dump in undrained crushed pineapple and spread to fill corners.
Then dump in cherry pie filling and spread around evenly.
Dump in dry cake mix; sprinkle it to cover evenly.
Scatter nuts over cake mix.
Cut butter into patties and place on top.
Do not mix ingredients, dumping does it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until nicely browned.

title: zucchini burger
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into burger size.
Bake 15 minutes on each side or until brown at 350°.
Good for picnics or to work.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Flour and season chops to taste.
Brown in bacon drippings and drain off excess fat.
Combine next 5 ingredients and cook to a syrup.
Then add onion and pepper.
Simmer chops in sauce 1 hour.

title: cool carrot salad
directions: In a 2-quart glass container with tight fitting lid, layer cooked carrots, green pepper slivers and onion rings; set aside.

title: chili sauce
directions: Boil until thick, approximately 3 hours.
Put into jars.
Seal. Yields 3 pints.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix with mixer and pour into ice cream maker.
Pour ice and rock salt over container and mix until firm.

title: pressed chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add mayonnaise and last the gelatin which has been dissolved in hot broth.
Put into 3 round quart cartons. Chill in refrigerator.
When thoroughly chilled, take out of cartons and slice.
Will serve 30.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
Pour melted butter over flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: four layer lemon delight
directions: Mix the above ingredients together with fork like pie crust. Press into the bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2 inch shallow pan 35 minutes at 325°.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shells slightly; let cool.
Blend cheese and mayonnaise and set aside.
Drain tomatoes well.
Layer tomatoes in pie shell with salt, pepper, onions, herbs and sausage.
Top with blended cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 2 pies.
(You can add more tomatoes, if needed.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Mix in sour cream and soup.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Sprinkle poppy seed over the mixture, then pour melted butter over it all.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: garlic mashed potatoes with skins
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Drain.
In large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, butter, cream cheese, garlic and scallions. Blend with mixer; adding milk to desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves approximately 10-12.

title: apple cheese salad
directions: Pour hot water over cinnamon candies.
Stir until they completely dissolve.
Add jello; stir until it completely dissolves.
Add applesauce and blend well.
Pour half of mixture in 8-inch square pan.
Let chill until firm.
Blend together cream cheese at room temperature, nuts and celery.
Add salad dressing. Spread over firm layer of apple mixture.
Pour on remaining apple mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut out in squares.
It's good on lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: classic sour cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cookie crumbs and butter or margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form cake pan.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk and beat until smooth. Beat in eggs, then sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned around the edge.
(Center will be slightly soft.)
Cool completely.
Top with cherry pie filling or other type you like. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together into a cookie dough.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Make into small balls and bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix and bake in pie plate 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cover with whipped cream to serve.

title: bob's surprise
directions: Chop up carrots, celery and onions; quarter potatoes.
Line roasting pan with choice of meat.
Put a little of barbecue and all other seasoning over meat.
Layer carrots, celery, onions and potatoes over meat, adding sauce and seasoning to suit taste. Bake covered at 375° until celery is tender.

title: fort worth tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocado with lemon juice, salt and pepper in a bowl.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix. Coarsely chop tomatoes and black olives.
On a large platter, layer in this order: bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, green onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box
and set aside to let cool. Mix pudding as directed on box and add Cool Whip; mix. When cake is fully cooled, cut into squares and set aside.

title: sausalito crab dip
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
(Can be heated, if desired.)
Serve with crackers, etc.

title: chicken mami
directions: Boil linguini pasta (Mami) until cooked.
Put pasta on a large colander and place under cold running water.
Set aside.

title: baked cherry pudding
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine pineapple with its own juice and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce top with a fork at 1-inch intervals.
Pour on pineapple mixture and spread evenly over cake. Cool completely.

title: michael's apple crisp
directions: In bowl, combine sugars, flour, oats and spice.
Cut in margarine (or butter) until mix resembles coarse crumbs.
Butter a round micro-safe baking dish.
Place apples in dish; drizzle with apple juice (or water).
Sprinkle with topping.
Micro uncovered on High power, 14 to 16 minutes, turning once.
Do not put in refrigerator or cover because the topping will become soggy.
(In case it does get soggy, it's good that way, too!)

title: quick chicken stir fry
directions: In wok or deep sided 12 inch skillet, heat oil over medium high heat. Add chicken, stir fry 2 minutes or until no longer pink in center.
Add frozen vegetables, cover and cook 4 minutes, stirring occasionally. In small bowl, combine soy sauce, pineapple juice and cornstarch.
Pour over chicken and vegetables, cook 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve immediately over rice.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Measure and sift together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Stir in sweetener, cranberries, nuts and orange peel. Combine orange juice, egg and salad oil, add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool and serve. Eighteen slices; 1 slice equals 93 calories.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased long casserole (at least 2 quarts).
Top with paprika and more grated cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350°
for approximately 45 minutes.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water in a large bowl.
Stir in cranberry sauce and break up into gelatin mixture.
Add pineapple and 1/2 cup walnuts and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef with onion, salt and garlic powder. Add red chili sauce and simmer until tender.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and shape into round ball.
Chill. (Can be made a day ahead.)
Mix together the chili sauce and horseradish.
Pour on top of mixture when ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish, put rice, beef broth, 1 soup can water, carrots, onions, steak sauce, salt, pepper and basil.
Arrange pork chops over rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 10 minutes more or until all water is absorbed.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut into small pieces.
Spread evenly in a 12 x 9-inch pan.
In pot, bring to a boil the chicken broth, soup, salt and pepper; pour over chicken.

title: macaroni and cheese(family style)
directions: Lightly brown ham in butter.
Stir in soup, milk and 3/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring often.
Blend sauce with macaroni; pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until browned and bubbling.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand overnight.
Put on stove and boil for 25 minutes.
Take off stove and stir in 2 small boxes of strawberry Jell-O or 1 large box of Jell-O.
Put in jars and seal.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stir in cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Combine chilled gelatin and pudding in a bowl. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Chill until mixture mounds when spooned.
Fold in apple, celery and nuts.
Pour into a mold. Chill until firm, 6 hours or overnight.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix butter and flour until resembles fine crumbs. Add cream; mix and pat into a greased 9 x 9 pan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Pour 1 quart of fresh fruit over crust.

title: lemon marinade barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow baking dish.
Combine all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 6 hours or overnight, turning chicken often. Place on grill brushing with marinade.
Grill on each side 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Chicken may be cooked in oven at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cocoa butter syrup
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Add vanilla; continue to simmer over medium heat until thick.

title: vegetable combo
directions: Slice ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt, lemon pepper and lots of oleo.
Wrap in foil.
Cook at 350° about 1 hour in oven or on grill.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box. Grease and flour 9 X 13 cake pan. Cover bottom of pan with coconut and chopped nuts. Spoon cake mix over. Mix margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy. Spoon in globs on top of cake mix. Bake about 35 to 40 minutes at 350.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt Hershey bars.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes to cool.
Mix Hershey bars and chocolate syrup.
Then mix with Cool Whip.
Cut angel food cake into 3 layers.
Frost cake and refrigerate.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions, salt and drain.
Mix in tomatoes. Boil noodles until tender (drain).
Mix into other mixture in baking dish pour in mixture.
Top with sliced velveeta cheese and add crackers on top.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash banana with fork.
Blend in sugar, salt and beaten egg. Melt butter and stir into banana mixture.
Dissolve soda in water and add to sifted flour.
Mix and bake in loaf pan for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Put the salt over them and mix up.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, wash and drain.
Squeeze all juice out.
Put in pot.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: fudge mallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate pieces with peanut butter in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares. Makes 2 dozen.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and lard with 2 knives (or hands).
Put 1 egg in a cup with 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Fill with milk to make 1 cup. Add to flour mixture.
Makes 3 double crust pies.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add sour milk and vanilla.
Add flour to mixture.
Make cocoa and food coloring into paste.
Mix the vinegar and soda, then fold into other ingredients. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Use "Airport Frosting."

title: tom's honey chicken
directions: Mix together flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Coat chicken in flour mixture.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Roll chicken in butter and place all pieces in the baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel sauce for red velvet cake(can be used on any cake.)
directions: Mix all and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes. It can bubble, but do not boil. Serve warm over cake with whipped cream. This can be made ahead and slowly reheated before serving.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly. Put in loaf pan and cover with bacon.
Pour the tomato sauce over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in apples.
Pour into pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until done. Cool and frost with vanilla icing and sprinkle with nuts.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix well.
Use 1/3 cup mix and hot water to make hot chocolate.

title: peppermint's v-8 chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, garlic and parsley; drain.
Return to pot.
Combine all other ingredients.
Simmer for at least 3 hours. Serve with cheese (optional).

title: baked mustard chicken
directions: Brush chicken with mustard and dredge in bread crumbs.
Place in a baking dish.
Combine butter, lemon juice and water; drizzle one tablespoon over each piece of chicken and pour remainder in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered.
Remove cover; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 15 more minutes.

title: fabulous corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Add chiles, cheeses and corn.
Stir in dry ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
In oven, bake at 350° for 1 hour.
In microwave, bake on High for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate filled snowballs
directions: Mix well the margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Shape dough around a chocolate kiss.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes on ungreased sheet.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.

title: wassail
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Heat to a boil; simmer 20 minutes and keep warm (works good in crock-pot).

title: cucumber pickles(refrigerated)
directions: Sprinkle salt over cukes and onions and let stand for 2 hours. Rinse in colander.
Boil vinegar and sugar.
Pour over cukes and let stand several days.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Blend together milk, strawberries and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and place in freezer until congealed, then take out, mix gently and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Prepare jello, using about 1/4 cup less water than usual.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan and chill until firm.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg; pat in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix frosting and cream cheese; reserve 1/2 cup. To the remainder, add eggs. Mix well and put on top of cake mix mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When cool, frost with 1/2 cup frosting.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Place six slices of bread on bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup Cheddar cheese, broccoli, ham and remaining bread slices cut in half diagonally.

title: microwave chocolate oatrage snake cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate morsels.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.
Spread batter into 8-inch square microwavable dish; cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High 4 minutes; rotate dish 1/4 turn.
Microwave at High an additional 4 to 5 minutes or until top appears dry.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate morsels over top of warm cake.
Let stand 10 minutes; spread over cake.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 12 squares.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix corn and flour.
Mix oleo and cheese.
Mix all together, except for peppers.
Add peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions with a little water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Pour into a colander to drain.
When well drained, mash squash and onions with margarine.
Add salt, pepper, egg, and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Must be made one day in advance.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips; dredge in flour.
Combine steak, broth, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in 2 1/2-quart micro-proof casserole.
Push meat to center of casserole; set aside.
Wipe mushrooms with damp towel.
Cut into thick slices.
Arrange mushrooms and onion around meat.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on 80 for 7 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in sour cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk, then mix cream cheese and Cool Whip. Combine together.
Crush cookies.
Put a layer of cookies in pan, a layer of mixture, then another layer of cookies.

title: august moon fried rice
directions: Slice all vegetables on the diagonal. In a large skillet or Dutch oven, heat oil and add vegetables; stir fry for 3 to 4 minutes.
Reduce heat and stir in rice.
Add meat and seasonings; mix until blended.
Add soy sauce and stir through.

title: oriental salad(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Combine sugar, olive oil, beef flavoring and white vinegar. Refrigerate until ready to pour on salad.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and mix well.

title: chocolate-hazelnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Beat butter and sugars; add chocolate-hazelnut spread and chocolate. Add vanilla; beat. Add eggs. Combine flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in any remaining flour. Stir in chocolate pieces and hazelnuts. Drop 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes. Drizzle cooled cookies with white chocolate. Let stand until chocolate is set.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine jello and water until dissolved. Then fold in all at once the strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn 1/2 of this mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish for the first layer.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Evenly spread the sour cream over the first layer.
Spoon the rest of the strawberry mixture on and refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli; cut into very small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: frosty cranberry salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Pour mixture in an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: avocado dressing and dip
directions: In a food processor, combine the first 6 ingredients and blend 2 minutes at low speed.
Add mayonnaise and blend 1/2 minute at low speed, then increase speed to medium and blend an additional 2 minutes.
Slowly add avocados and blend at low speed no longer than 4 minutes.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Use as a salad dressing, dip for vegetables or crackers, or on bread for a sandwich.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a large pot.
Cook 1 hour over medium heat.
This will make a roaster pan full.
Can be frozen.

title: homemade sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage; add other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender and flavors are blended.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well. Add pumpkin and water.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder; add to pumpkin mixture.

title: salsa
directions: Chop whole tomatoes to desired size; return to juice.
Mix with olives.
Chop green onions into small size pieces.
Use some of the tops; add to mixture.
Use 1 1/2 rounded teaspoons of chilies; add to mixture.
Add more chilies by small amount to make hotter.
Prepare in the evening, reserving chilies.
Add chilies to the mixture the morning of the event.

title: square chocolate bit
directions: Mix butter, cocoa, water, sugar and eggs in casserole.
Place on light fire, boiling 1 minute.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix in vanilla.
Place in square dishes of 8-inch.
Cool off and frost or use your own choice of icing.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Let potatoes thaw about 2 hours.
Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Fold in grated cheese and sour cream.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle topping over potatoes.

title: lemon, lime and cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix the jello with the hot water.
Dissolve and let cool. Mix the cool jello with the following:
cottage cheese, crushed pineapple, mayonnaise, milk and pecans.
Refrigerate overnight. Serves 6.

title: oat bran pancakes
directions: Place dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir to mix.
Make a well in center; place oil, egg and water in well.
Mix to form batter.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Cook until thick and clear.
Let cool.
Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour filling over strawberries.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham crackers.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: microwave nachos
directions: Spread chips out on a plate.
Cover with cheese.
Cook in microwave for 45 seconds.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream and mashed graham crackers, then add the other ingredients and pack in cake pan for 3 days in refrigerator.

title: good puffy fritters(serves 4)
directions: Sift
together flour, baking powder and salt. Beat eggs with milk.
Stir remaining ingredients into egg mixture. Beat until smooth
and well blended. Fold in desired vegetables or fruit. Drop by tablespoonfuls into deep oil at 375°. Fry until golden brown.
Remove
with
a
slotted spoon. Drain on paper towel.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Mash 1 can of the beans until smooth.
In large soup pot, cook ham, celery, carrots, onion, zucchini, basil and pepper in olive oil until vegetables are tender and begin to brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, chicken broth, spinach, mashed white beans and 2 cups water; over high heat, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining beans; heat through.
Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients. Cook broccoli and drain well, then mix broccoli with the other ingredients.
Pour into a cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip - vero beach
directions: Drain spinach in colander and press dry with paper towel.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, lightly saute peppers and onion in oil.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Cook. Blend thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and mix well. In a 2-quart casserole, layer 1 cup corn, 1/2 of meat mixture, 1/2 of tomatoes and repeat corn, meat and tomatoes.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: cherry salad mold
directions: Combine cherry jello, sour cherries, sugar and Coke.
Heat to boil and let thicken slightly.
Add pineapple and nuts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish, cover top with ketchup.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 44 - 50 min., halfway through the baking process, drain the grease.

title: ham and egg surprise(for brunch)
directions: Put half of the cubes of bread in bottom of casserole.
Add ham and half of the cheese. Add remaining bread and cheese.
Pour well beaten egg mixture (eggs, salt, dry mustard and milk) over top and push down (with hands), soaking mixture well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, until golden brown and bubbly.

title: broccoli mushroom casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Preheat oven at 350°. Combine mayonnaise, cheese, eggs, soup and onion juice.
Fold in broccoli.
Top with crumbs, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 45 minutes, or in microwave, on High for 23 minutes or less.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti, don't overcook.
Mix soup and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 1 quart greased container.
Add a little more cheese on top.

title: minute cranberry salad
directions: Make jello with the boiling water and cool to syrup consistency. Add cranberry sauce, marmalade, almonds and rum. Beat well.
Pour into molds and cool until firm.

title: old-fashioned fig jam
directions: Mix these thoroughly and add Tears of Joy and Sorrow and Sympathy for Others.
Fold in four cups of Prayers and Faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of Christian living.
After pouring all into your daily life, bake well with the heat of Kindness and serve with a Smile.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all except bananas and chill.
Put the bananas in the pineapple juice for 5 to 10 minutes.
Right before serving, drain bananas and add them.

title: carolyn's chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 350 till bubbly about 20 minutes.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients until dough forms a ball. Shape into balls, using 1 teaspoon dough for each ball.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten to about 2 inches with hand. Bake 8 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: great cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers.

title: tuna melts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except rolls.
Fill rolls with tuna mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until heated through.

title: the ultimate tossed salad
directions: First I wash each of the following:
lettuce, tomatoes, green pepper and celery stalks.
In a large or small bowl I choose to start with the romaine lettuce instead of iceberg because there are more vitamins in romaine than iceberg.

I select a few leaves, depending on the size bowl I use and then proceed to cut each lettuce leaf into 3 or 4 large pieces, then I cut my tomatoes in half and then into half again (quarters) into 3 or 4 pieces.
Next comes the green pepper from which I remove the stem, seeds and veins.
Cut the green pepper in half and into as many as possible strips; cut into bite-size pieces.
With cucumber I cut down until I start seeing seeds.
I stripe my cucumber and then cut in half or in whole pieces.

title: grab n' go breakfast muffins
directions: Stir flour, cereal, sugar, and baking powder together in a large bowl.

title: banana bread with coconut
directions: Mix sugar and butter well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add bananas.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add coconut, nuts and flavoring.

title: mom's coleslaw
directions: Crisp the
shredded
cabbage
in
ice water for 1 hour; drain well.
Mix with peppers.
Combine the mayo, lemon juice, onion, celery
seed, sugar, salt and pepper; mix with cabbage. Stir in dry roasted peanuts.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add oatmeal.
Mix (it takes awhile) and press into shallow cooking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Melt 6 to 8 ounces of chocolate in a double boiler.
Add milk, if needed.
Spread over the oatmeal mix.
Cut into cookies only after completely cooled.

title: basque potatoes
directions: Saute onion, celery, carrot and garlic in melted butter until tender.
Combine chicken broth with enough water to make 2 cups. Add broth, potatoes, salt and pepper to sauteed vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove cover.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until broth is thickened.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container. Put 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to mug.
Add hot water and stir.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, mix brown sugar and cocoa.
Stir in water. Add marshmallows.
Spoon over this the devil's food cake batter.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Really works.
Good!

title: orange bread
directions: Cover orange peel with water and 1/4 teaspoon baking soda; cook until tender and drain, then wash with clear water.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water to orange peel and cook until thick. Set aside to cool.
Mix together flour, sugar, butter, eggs, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and orange peel.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix well.
Let set overnight or make it early in the morning.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, beat well. Sift flour, mix water with vanilla.
Add alternately with flour until well blended.
Melt butter in large skillet, with brown sugar until sugar is melted.
Arrange pineapple slices adding cherries in center.
Spread batter over pineapple.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Dust pork chops with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Place chops in baking dish and arrange sliced onions on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chops.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll each piece in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Drop into Bundt pan.
In a small saucepan, melt brown sugar and margarine.
Pour this over biscuits in Bundt pan.
Put in cold oven and turn on to 350°.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.
This is a beautiful and good breakfast, easy and inexpensive.
Also the children love to help make it.

title: camp stew
directions: Put all the meat into large pressure cooker and cover with water.
Pressure until done.
Take bones out of chicken and shred all meat together back into broth where it was cooked.
Add onions, potatoes, tomatoes and corn.
Cook slowly until done and thick.
Add ketchup and cook another 15 minutes.
Add chili powder as you add ketchup.
Stir often as it will stick quickly.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: In a bowl, combine the eggs and tomato juice.
Stir in bread crumbs, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add ground beef; mix well.
On wax paper or foil, pat meat to a 10 x 8 inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top of meat, leaving a small margin around.
Reserve 1 slice of cheese.
Tear up remainder of cheese; sprinkle over ham.
Starting with short end, carefully roll up meat using paper to lift; seal edges and ends.
Place roll seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 1/4 hours.
(Center will be pink due to ham.)
Cut reserved cheese slice into 4 triangles and overlap atop meat. Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: finger cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pinch off.
Roll size of finger.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine in pan and brown; cool and set aside.

title: rotel
directions: Combine ingredients in large crock-pot.

title: heath cookies
directions: Cook butter, margarine and sugar for 3 minutes.
Place divided graham crackers very close together on jelly roll pan.
Pour cooked mixture over crackers and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Allow cookies to cool and remove each cookie from pan.

title: fresh homemade apple pie
directions: Put sliced apples into pie shell.
Sprinkle with allspice. Mix sugar and flour together.
Pour over apples.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except crab and Cheddar cheese.
Add 4 ounces Cheddar cheese and crab.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick coconut crust
directions: Mix butter and coconut.
Press evenly in 9-inch pie pan. Bake in a slow oven (300°) until light brown, 30 to 35 minutes or brown coconut mixture lightly in skillet for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Press evenly in a pie pan.
Fill cooled crust with ice cream, a cream or chiffon filling.

title: beef summer sausage
directions: Combine the above ingredients and mix well.
Form mixture into a large roll.
Wrap in foil.
Place in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Poke holes in the foil with a fork along the bottom and place in a baking dish with a little water.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oatmeal with boiling water.
Let sit for 20 minutes. Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Alternate adding flour mixture and oatmeal with shortening mixture, blending well. Place into a greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350 degrees.
Mix together margarine, 1/2 c. brown sugar, evaporated milk, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Spread on hot cake. Bake until brown at 350 degrees for 10 - 15 minutes.

title: carrots with aceto balsamic vinegar
directions: Place carrots in the 1/4 cup water.
Add butter and salt. Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Carrots should have absorbed water.
Combine the brown sugar, water and vinegar in a saucepan.
Cook until well blended and pour over carrots.
Serves 4.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Skin and cut up chicken.
Put in pot of water (cover chicken with water) and let cook.
When chicken is done, cool, debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook dumpling noodles and drain.
Put chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Put noodles on top of chicken.
Pour soups and sour cream over noodles.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: survival sandwich
directions: Distribute peanut butter evenly on one slice of bread using a clean knife.
Repeat procedure using the other slice of bread and jelly.
Smash or squish both pieces of bread together (this is best done while holding one slice in one hand and the other slice in the other hand and then making a big clapping motion).
The thinner the sandwich, the better the taste!!
Serve with potato chips and a cold glass of milk.

title: chip dip
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients in microwave until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese.
Add onion and pimentos.
Chill 6 hours. Add milk if too thick.

title: overnight hot dish
directions: Mix, cover, and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan (uncovered).
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pound cake(number of servings:  15 to 18)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco until sugar dissolves.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately to mixture.
Add flavorings.
Place in cold stove and turn oven to 325°; bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Peel and chop broccoli; use stems.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Chop onion.
Combine and toss with nuts.
Pour dressing over all and mix well.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms and beef in butter.
Transfer to large pot.
Add 1 cup boiling water and bouillon cubes.
Add tomato paste and dry mustard.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add sour cream; simmer 5 minutes more.
Add flour and water to thicken.
Serve over noodles.
Serve rolls as well.

title: wisconsin chicken stew
directions: Wash and cut up the chicken.
Place in a saucepot and cover with cold water.
Stir in mirepoix, bay leaf and pepper and bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and allow to simmer until the chicken is tender.
This should take approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove the chicken from the stock (cooking liquid) and strain to remove the mirepoix.
Discard mirepoix and return the stock to a simmer.
Slowly thicken with roux to a medium consistency.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the potatoes, white sugar, eggs, 1 stick butter and vanilla together.
Put in a casserole pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Sprinkle over the potatoes.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients in order given.
Combine and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and shakes a little in the center.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Can be prepared and refrigerated for 24 hours before baking. Brown meat and chopped onion until almost done.

Add taco sauce, enchilada sauce, and soup and mix well. Layer in a greased 13 X 9 x 2 inch pan. Start with a little meat sauce mixture on the bottom; then add tortillas, cheese, meat mix, tortillas, meat, and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will need 8 popsicle sticks.

title: rancheros casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Mix potatoes, water, corn and milk in 2 quart casserole dish.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Add taco seasoning to beef.	Stir into potatoes.
Add shredded cheese. Bake uncovered 30-35 minutes until top is brown.
Top with salsa and sour cream after serving on plates.
Serves 6.

title: amelia's chicken
directions: Soak the chicken in a pan of water to which 2 tablespoons white vinegar and 4 tablespoons salt have been added.
After 1 hour, drain and wipe dry.

title: frizzled tomatoes
directions: Use about twice as many tomatoes as you think your family will eat.

title: marinade for marinated mushrooms
directions: Slice mushrooms and put in glass jar.
Cover with marinade mix and leave for at least one week.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended and smooth. Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Use to dip cookies, cake cubes, fruit, pretzels, etc.

title: scalloped pineapple(great with ham)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add egg with vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: red punch
directions: Mix boiling water and jello in container and set aside.
In large container mix Kool-Aid with 2 quarts water and add sugar. Mix in orange pineapple drink and jello mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving add vanilla ice cream and 7-Up.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Thoroughly combine ingredients in a bowl.
Store in an airtight container.
For a single serving put 1/4 cup mixture in a cup and add 6 ounces boiling water.
Add miniature marshmallows and stir until blended.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Mix 2 level teaspoons mix for every 1 cup hot water.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel, cube and boil potatoes for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and milk, gradually, a little at a time.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Remove from heat.
Place potatoes in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: green chili rellenos casserole
directions: Cook hamburger.
Make layers of chilies, meat and cheese. Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over layers.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted margarine mixed together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: steak bake
directions: Slice steak in 1-inch slices.
Brown in hot oil on both sides. Layer in baking dish.
Pour soup and water over steak.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: sunny italy dressing
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: chocolate peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt 2 sticks oleo and cocoa; set aside to cool. With electric mixer, beat sugar, eggs, flour, salt and vanilla; add cooled chocolate mixture to this and blend well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° about 20 minutes (check with toothpick). While hot, spread on crunchy peanut butter; let cool, then pour on icing. Can be frozen.

title: boston-style fish chowder
directions: In large Dutch oven, cook bacon till crisp; remove and crumble.
In drippings, cook celery, onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add water and bouillon, stirring until smooth and well blended.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; reduce heat and cook 10 mins.
Stir in fish; cook 15 mins. longer.
Add cream and pimiento;
heat through.
Garnish with bacon.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake
potatoes.
Cut
in
half and carefully remove the inside.
Mash the potatoes; add salt, pepper and sour cream if desired
(about
small container).
Put this mixture back into the potato shell and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Put in oven
and melt cheese just before serving.
Can be served with bacon bits or chives.

title: spaghetti sauce(all purpose sauce)
directions: Add meat to a pan and place in moderate 350° oven.

Let stay a few minutes, stirring a few times so that it will brown evenly. Heat the olive oil in a kettle, add onion, garlic and mushrooms. Cook and stir 5 minutes; add Burgundy, tomatoes, tomato puree and beef stock or bouillon.
Let cook gently 10 minutes; add the meat. Add spices; let simmer 1 1/2 hours, skimming occasionally.

title: danish potato soup
directions: Put onion in blender with water and puree.
Peel, quarter and rinse potatoes.
Boil until soft, then mash while still in water. Add salt and onions to potatoes (leave all liquids in).
Put tomatoes in blender and puree.
Add to potatoes.
Separately cook fish until flaky.
Add all final ingredients and add water until consistency of soup.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a pan, brown hamburg and 1/2 onion; remove from heat and cool.
Mix corn bread mix with eggs and margarine; mix well.
Add green chilies, corn and onion.
Stir well.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, put half corn bread mix and meat and cheese.
Put rest of corn bread mix on top.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: german potato salad(microwave)
directions: Place bacon in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High until crisp.
Remove; crumble and set aside.
Add onion to bacon drippings.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Microwave 1 minute on High.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High until mixture boils.
Add potatoes and bacon; stir gently to coat with sauce.
Serve at room temperature or warm.

title: shrimp-cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Or use to stuff celery or with fresh veggies for dip.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Note: Use a double boiler.

title: skor bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in jelly roll pan and cut into cubes. Mix pudding mix with milk and Kahlua.
Add Cool Whip to pudding mix.
Layer 1/3 cake cubes, 1/3 pudding and 1/3 candy bars in large glass bowl.
Repeat, ending with the candy on top. Refrigerate several hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed, no salt.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli after draining.
Top with croutons or cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: orange tea by jennie
directions: Mix Crystal Light iced tea mix in 1 gallon cold water.
Add frozen orange juice concentrate.
Mix well.
Add ice cubes. Refrigerate and serve.

title: busy day meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, salad dressing mix, eggs, bread crumbs and green pepper.
Shape into loaf in greased shallow baking dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4
ingredients
in mixer bowl. Beat until crumbly.
Press into
large
spring-form
pan or (9 x 13-inch) baking pan.
Beat 2
eggs with cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons of
vanilla
until
fluffy.
Spread
over cake mix layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Blend sour cream with 1
teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread over top.
Pour
pie
filling
(cherry, blueberry, strawberry, etc.) over cheesecake and chill.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: cream cheese pineapple salad
directions: Soak gelatine 5 minutes in cold water, then add hot water and beat in cream cheese.
Add sugar, whipped cream and pineapple. Add nuts and salt last.
Pour into molds and let congeal.
This will make 2 small molds or one large.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in water until tender; drain. Melt butter and add to squash. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Brown beef well with onions in skillet. Season to taste. Mix squash and beef together. Beat eggs and mayonnaise together. Add to beef/squash mixture. Stir well and add cheese. Pour into casserole dish and cover with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine dry ingredients. Mix well. In mixing bowl, combine shortening and eggs. Mix on medium speed until blended. Add brown sugar and vanilla. Blend well. Add dry ingredients. Finally add oats and raisins. The mixture will be very thick. You may have to mix by hand. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients, pour over shredded cabbage.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla. Mix well.

title: honey graham bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, combine crumbs, Eagle Brand, honey and orange juice; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan and bake for 25 minutes. Cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars and store at room temperature.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown onion, bacon and garlic together.
Add other ingredients except beans and simmer together for 20 minutes.
Add beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar and poppy seed in a bowl.
Make a well in the center of these ingredients and add remaining ingredients into the well.
Stir only until moistened.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in muffin cups.

title: do not peek chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour melted margarine and soup/milk mixture over top of rice.
Lay chicken on rice and sprinkle onion soup. Seal with foil. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325° (do not peek).

title: pasta salad
directions: Dice ham, salami and cheese.
Chop green peppers.
Boil shells as directed on package.
Rinse with cold water.
Add all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground chuck in a large pot.
Drain meat.
Add Prego sauce and water to meat and stir together.
Spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Put a layer of meat sauce to cover the bottom of the pan.
Next, alternate layers of dry noodles, sauce and shredded cheese until all ingredients are used and ending with the cheese layer.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 hungry adults.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Scramble eggs with a small amount of water in a bowl; wash chicken then dip in eggs then in bread crumbs mixed with Parmesan cheese.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Thaw raspberries.
Cook 10 minutes.
Rub through strainer with a wooden spoon; cool.
Add thawed lemonade concentrate.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale, chilled.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cook, stirring constantly until the mixture boils.
Put into casserole and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peach freeze
directions: Mix and freeze.
Place several scoops in a glass.
Pour clear soda over.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine soup, milk, mayonnaise, celery, onion and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in cheese, shrimp and cooked noodles to soup and milk mix.
Mix.

title: frosty chocolate souffle(dessert)
directions: Whip the cream until very stiff.
Fold in the chocolate ice cream topping or syrup and creme de cacao thoroughly.
Turn into individual souffle cups or line muffin tins with paper cupcake liners and fill with the mixture.
Cover; freeze until firm, 2 to 4 hours.
Serve frozen topped with chocolate shavings.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan with the 2 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream butter; gradually add balance of sugar.
Beat after each addition, add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating until well blended.
Dredge blueberries with remaining 1/4 cup flour.
Fold berries into batter.
Pour into prepared pan.
