Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans.
Pour in container and garnish top with pecans.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Peel and slice apples; set aside.
Mix the flour, 2 tablespoons of sugar, salt and butter with pie blender and pat in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In a large mixing bowl, mix apples with 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Spread on crust.
Bake at 325° until tender.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook and cut chicken in fine pieces.
Save 1 quart of broth. Break spaghetti in small pieces.
Add to broth.
Cook and drain. Heat onion and green pepper in oleo.
Add soup, can of milk, pimentos (drained), salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbles and browns.

title: peanut patties
directions: Stir together and bring to a boil the sugar, syrup and water. Add food color and peanuts.
Let mixture cook until it reaches hard ball stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour on a buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix and
pour into long pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: bacon cheese balls
directions: In a mixing bowl beat cream cheese, cheddar cheese and pepper until blended.
Stir in broccoli.
Shape into a ball and roll in bacon.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: hungry jack beef and bean round-up
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar and beans.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: broccoli-pasta toss
directions: In a large saucepan, cook broccoli and pasta in a large amount of boiling water for 6 to 8 minutes or just until tender, stirring once or twice to prevent pasta from sticking.
Drain.
Add oil to pasta-vegetable mixture and toss.
Add Parmesan cheese, sesame seed, garlic powder and pepper.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all together.
Cook until thick.
Cool and add 1 pint fresh strawberries.
Put into baked pie shell.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: apricot orange jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and apricots and save juice.
Put jello in hot water and Marshmallow Creme.
Add 1 cup mixed juice.
Add diced apricots and pineapple.
Let jello set.

title: mindy's marvelous brownies
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup of boiling water; add fruits and nuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Set in refrigerator until partially firm.
Fold 1/2 of sour cream into remaining 1/2 jello mixture and pour it on top of the now firm first half.
Set in refrigerator to firm all, then spread remaining sour cream on top.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: garden quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix and water.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on cloth covered board. Knead 5 times.

title: homestyle rotini tuna bake
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients and 1 cup French fried onions.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes, or until heated thoroughly.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: daiquiri pie
directions: Mix pudding, gelatin and sugar in saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup water and eggs; blend well.
Add remaining water.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; stir in rum.
Chill about 1 1/2 hours.
To hasten chilling, place bowl of filling mixture in a large bowl of ice and water.
Stir until mixture is cold.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, lime or lemon slice, grated lime or lemon peel or graham cracker crumbs.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve as is or add small cherry jello to congeal.
Make a day or two ahead. Molds nicely.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Blend the sour cream, sugar and vanilla for 5 minutes.
Blend both mixtures together.
Place on your graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Open door slightly.
Leave in oven 1 hour.
Slice and serve with fruit topping.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Chill.
Roll into small balls.

title: creamy gelatin dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in marshmallows until melted. Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Add pineapple and cold water to gelatin mixture; mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; chill until cool. Add sliced bananas.

title: easy-baked cheesecake
directions: Combine margarine, graham cracker crumbs and sugar; pat firmly in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk; beat until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Let cool to room temperature; chill. Remove side of pan.
Spread sour cream over cheesecake.
Garnish as desired.

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Pour off water.
Cover with fresh water. Cook slowly, just below boiling point, test with needle.
When navy beans are soft, drain them.
Put half of beans in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients and cover with other half of beans.
Cover beans with boiling water, put pork on top, add a little ketchup to boiling water.
Cook at 300° for 3 to 5 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add oil and beaten egg.
Pare and slice apples.
Place in bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with the other 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon or nutmeg.
Cover with the flour mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fluff salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese until jello is thoroughly dissolved.
Then add pineapple.
Mix well.
Then add to Cool Whip. Fold together until smooth.
Refrigerate.
For extra color, add food coloring.
This is a different fluff every time you change the flavor of the jello!

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare the potatoes (mashed).
Stir in parsley flakes; set aside.
In an ungreased 10 x 13-inch glass pan, stir remaining ingredients.
Mound potatoes on meat mixture. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until potatoes brown slightly.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown onions and hamburger and drain fat off.
Mix rest of ingredients together in crock-pot.
Add hamburger and stir. Simmer on low 2 hours.

title: lemon angel food dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and 1 cup sugar; beat until smooth and glossy.
Bake in well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions, garlic and dill in butter.
When onions are soft, add water and potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add tamari, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and pepper.
Remove some of the potatoes and broth from the pot and blend thoroughly.

title: hot buffalo wings
directions: Cut wings in half and discard tips which have been cut off. Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper.
Heat 2 inches of oil in large skillet to 350°.
Add chicken and fry 10 minutes, frying about a dozen at a time.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine hot sauce and remaining ingredients in a sauce pan, cook over low heat until margarine is melted.
In 13 x 3 inch dish arrange wings and then pour sauce over wings and bake uncovered at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put carrots in a 9-inch square casserole dish.
In large saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute celery and onion until tender-crisp.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until mixture is smooth.
Stir in milk and cook until mixture thickens.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Pour sauce over carrots.

title: seaweed soup
directions: Soak the dried seaweed in lukewarm water for 10 minutes and drain.
Fry the prepared seaweed and sliced beef with sesame oil and then pour water into the pan and boil it.
Add seasoning (soy sauce and garlic) into the soup and boil for another 10 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar; boil for 2 minutes.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Cool completely and add powdered sugar to desired consistency (about 1 box).
This icing is very good and doesn't get too hard.

title: frosted chocolate brownie supreme
directions: Beat oleo with mixer until fluffy.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add egg whites, sour cream, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Stir well.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done in middle.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Spread creamy Chocolate Frosting over cooled brownies; cut into squares.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine and nuts.
Spread in dish reserving some crumbs for top.
Mix sugar, cool whip and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding mix and milk, beating 2 minutes at low speed.
Spread over 2nd layer. Top with 8 oz. cool whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and graham cracker crumbs. Chill and serve.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Roll into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Mix chopped cabbage, onion and bell pepper well.
Pour sugar over mixture.
Do not stir.
Combine remaining ingredients in pan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer lettuce and vegetables in a flat container.
Top with mayonnaise.
Combine sugar, salt and garlic powder; sprinkle over mayonnaise.

title: bulgar primavera salad(tabouli)
directions: Place bulgar in large, heatproof bowl.
Bring water to boiling.
Pour over bulgar.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain bulgar thoroughly.
Return bulgar to large bowl.
Add tomatoes, currants, sunflower seeds, carrot, green onion, garlic, mint, basil and oregano.
Whisk together tamari, vinegar and oil in small bowl. Pour over bulgar mixture.
Mix well.

title: chicken gourmet
directions: Cook chicken and debone it.
Shred into pieces and place in square or 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: easy linguini with red clam sauce
directions: Scrub clams and set aside.
Saute garlic in oil for 1 minute. Add wine and next 3 ingredients and bring to boil.
Add clams, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until clams open. While sauce simmers, cook linguini.
Divide linguini into large soups bowls and top with sauce and add cheese if so choose.

title: super hershey bar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Gradually add flour and vanilla. Add eggs and oatmeal with salt, baking powder and baking soda, mixing well. Melt chips and candy bars, then add pecans. Mixture will be stiff. Mix with hands. Put on cookie sheet in small balls about 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Let cool and remove from cookie sheet.

title: amish style baked beans
directions: Drain beans and mix together.
Fry, but don't brown bacon.
Add beans, bacon and onions to casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Crush peanuts and sprinkle half over bottom of pie crust. Swirl small amount of peanut butter through softened ice cream. Spread in pie crust.
Sprinkle more crushed salted peanuts over ice cream.
Freeze.

title: kate's pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with Chef Paul's Magic barbecue seasoning. Let stand for 30 minutes. In frying pan, brown roast on all sides. Put roast in crock-pot. Cook until tender. Saute cubed potatoes in butter until tender. Add onions and mushrooms. Add to roast about 30 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Slightly flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for around 10 minutes or until brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze out water.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream, water chestnuts, soup mix and green onions.
Cut off top of bread and hollow out center of loaf.
Place dip into hollowed out center. Place torn out bread pieces outside of the loaf.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown first three ingredients and drain fat.
Add next 6 ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles, about 2 1/2 cups cooked, in salt water.
Drain.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.

title: peach jam
directions: You also need jars and lids (in boiling water before filling).

title: saucy pork chop dinner
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour; brown in heavy skillet.
Combine onions, green peppers, pineapple juice, catsup and Tabasco sauce.
Pour this mixture over meat.
Cover; cook slowly for about 1 hour, or until chops are thoroughly done. Serve chops with sauce over hot rice.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: salmon burgers
directions: In medium bowl combine salmon, mayonnaise, egg, lemon juice, bread crumbs, onion, parsley and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 burgers (mixture will be moist).
Heat 1 to 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet.
Place burgers in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Serve on bun with your favorite sauce.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Let cool.
Beat egg and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.

title: smothered steak
directions: Season steak with salt and pepper; flour and brown steak. Place in iron Dutch oven; pour small amount of water over steak. Turn fire real low, cover with lid and cook until tender.
She also cooked her chicken this way.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken and dipping sauce. Mix well. Cut chicken breasts in nugget size pieces.
Dip nuggets in batter and fry in hot oil (375°). Drain on paper towels and dip in favorite sauce.

title: sopa-de-fideo
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 300°.
Melt shortening. Saute vermicelli until browned.
Stir in meat and cook until it loses its red color.
Stir in salt, pepper, garlic salt, onions, celery, green pepper, corn and chili powder.
Add tomatoes and water, stirring gently.
Set temperature to 200°.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.
Place cheese slices on top and melt.
Serves 8.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rainbow rotini as directed and drain.
Mix vegetables and cheese in desired amount with the rotini.
Add Zesty Italian dressing and toss together.
Refrigerate.

title: pomegranate salad
directions: Dissolve jello according to package.
Refrigerate.
When starting to jell, add pineapple and pomegranate kernels.
Pour into desired mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Top with mixture of sour cream and mayonnaise.

title: sugar roasted nuts
directions: Boil until sugar has melted.
Add nuts to mixture.
Put in sheet pan and bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir occasionally.

title: phyllis' o'henry bars
directions: Melt sugar in light Karo syrup.
When it reaches a boil, remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Stir in Rice Krispies. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use wax paper to press so it will not stick to fingers.

title: hot spicy orange tea mix
directions: Add all ingredients to blender.
Cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Wait a few seconds before removing cover, for mix to settle.

title: lindberg special relish
directions: Grind all vegetables and add 1/3 cup salt.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Need not be cooked or sealed.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add brown sugar. Combine egg and milk; add milk mixture and shortening to flour. Mix enough to dampen flour.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate crinkle-top cookies(from nestle's chocolate chip bag)
directions: Microwave 1 cup morsels in medium microsafe bowl on High for 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a small bowl.
Beat granulated sugar, butter and vanilla in large mixer bowl until crumbly.
Beat in melted chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining morsels.
Cover, just until firm (about 2 hours).
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until sides are set, but centers are still soft.
Cool for 2 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: spicy peach jam
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar and bring to rolling boil. Stir constantly.
Add sugar.
Continue stirring.
Skim and ladle into 8 half-pint glasses.
Cover with 1/8-inch paraffin.

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add shortening, sugar and salt to milk. Cool. Add yeast; mix thoroughly. Add eggs.
Stir in enough flour to make stiff. Knead well on floured board.
Let rise slightly in greased bowl.
Roll out.
Cut and let rise 1 hour. Fry in hot fat and glaze while hot. Roll in powdered sugar and milk glaze.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat to cover baking sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip or margarine and salad dressing mix.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Top with vegetables and press down.
Chill for 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: vegetable manicotti
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package; drain. Rinse with cold water; drain. Spray 8 x 13 dishes with nonstick spray and arrange in single layer to fill.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening well.
Add sugar and cream well. Add eggs and cream until lemony colored.
Add flour, salt and baking powder, a little at a time.
Alternate with milk and add vanilla.
Grease and flour a tube pan thoroughly.
Place in a cold oven.
Set oven to 325°.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: rolls (made with water)
directions: Soak 2 packages yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
While yeast soaks, combine sugar, Crisco and salt; pour 1 cup boiling water over ingredients.
Add 1 cup flour and 1 cup cold water; let cool. When mixture is cool, add eggs.
Add yeast to cooled mixture. Lastly add 7 cups flour to mixture.
Place, covered, in refrigerator.
Roll out and make rolls about 1 to 1 1/2 hours before baking, letting them rise until double in size.
Bake in 400° to 425° oven until golden brown.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients together except for Parmesan cheese. Place in a small shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or microwave, covered, on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with grated cheese 5 minutes before done in oven and 1 minute in microwave so cheese can melt on top.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine the above ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with Fritos scoops or other chips.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes and crush garlic with press.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and microwave 3-5 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits or other snack crackers.

title: great grandma's gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten egg and molasses. Sift all dry ingredients and add.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Bake in greased pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Makes 15 pieces.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Cook roast until browned on all sides; spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 40 minutes or until roast and vegetables are tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Cook sauce until it thickens.
Serve with roast and vegetables.

title: meringue shells
directions: Add salt, vinegar and vanilla to egg whites; beat until mixture forms peaks.
Add sugar very gradually and continue beating until very stiff.
Spoon in mounds on cookie sheet covered with plain ungreased paper.
Shape 6 large cups with spoon.
Bake in slow oven (250° or 275°) for 45 minutes.
Remove from paper immediately. Cool.

title: texas chili
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until well mixed.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix and form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven until browned.

title: mushroom-stuffed beef roast
directions: Trim excess fat from roast.
Cut 8 crosswise slits or pockets in roast, 3-inches deep.
Place roast in plastic bag; set in a deep bowl.
Pour wine over roast; seal bag.
Marinate in refrigerator 6 to 24 hours, turning bag occasionally.

title: turnip green casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Top with buttered cracker crumbs and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: dip for strawberries
directions: Let cream cheese set to room temperature.
Mix together and chill in refrigerator.

title: family oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, molasses, egg and sugar.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold in oats and raisins.
Drop full teaspoons of batter onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add the rest of ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 350°
for 1 hour or in 3 layer pans for 30 minutes.
Grease and flour pans.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and green pepper until meat is done.
Drain off fat.
Add soups, spices and mushrooms to meat mixture.
Simmer on low heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Add meat mixture to noodles.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Pour jello over cheese layer and refrigerate until set.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In
a
mixing
bowl
mix
together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin
until light and fluffy.
Stir dry ingredients together. Add
to
pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Spread in greased 12 x
1-inch
pan.
Bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: bread pudding(serves 4)
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Fill with bread torn into cubes.
In mixing bowl, mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread sliced until moistened.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and 300° for 15 minutes longer.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut each pepper lengthwise in half.
Wash insides and outsides.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Cook pepper in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a saucepan, heat milk and butter to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in cooked rice and raisins.
In a bowl, add eggs and beat well.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Combine rice mixture and egg mixture.
Pour into greased 1-1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until firm.
Yield 4 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and store in refrigerator until chilled or overnight.
Slice 1/2-inch and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
You can add raisins.

title: peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla pudding, margarine, milk and egg for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 or 10-inch greased pie plate.
Arrange on top the peaches.
In a small bowl mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Spoon on top of the peaches to within 1-inch of the crust.
Be careful not to get too close to edge of plate.
Sprinkle the whole pie with a mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Stir applesauce into Jell-O mixture.
Chill until partly jelled.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Swirl through Jell-O; chill until set.

title: oriental chicken and noodles
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Heat oil in deep skillet and saute chicken in heated oil for 5 minutes. Add cabbage, celery and sprouts.
Mix well. Cover and cook over low heat 3 minutes. Cook noodles according to directions, then add noodles to chicken mixture.
In a separate bowl, mix together cornstarch and broth. Stir into chicken mixture until thickened.
Sprinkle with scallions, caraway seed and lemon juice.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 380 calories.

title: special k trail mix
directions: Melt margarine and stir in cinnamon.
Toss with cereal, pecans and pretzels.
Spread on baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for about 10 minutes, stirring once. Mix in raisins.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 6 cups.

title: hungry jack biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef; mix with beans in a casserole dish.
Add barbecue sauce and salt.
Mix together.
Cut biscuits in half and place around edge of dish.
Press down into mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: sweet corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, eggs, milk, salt, pepper and butter together.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Set casserole dish in a pan containing about 1 inch of hot water. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: In a 2-quart pan, empty crushed pineapple and juice and bring to a boil.
Add jello.
Mix well.
Cool.
Then add buttermilk and pecans.
Mix well.
Empty into dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: Pound chicken lightly to form 1/8-inch thick rectangles, bone side facing up.
Place 1 piece of Prosciutto on chicken piece, folding if too long.
Place 1 slice of cheese atop Prosciutto, closer to one edge.
Top with some tomato.
Fold in long sides of chicken and roll up jelly roll style, starting from edge with cheese.
Secure with wooden toothpicks.

title: fudgemellows
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in microwave. Stir and fold in marshmallows. Pour in buttered pan. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Cut into squares and eat! Crunchy peanut butter will add nuts.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender; debone and place in oblong baking dish.
Cover the chicken with Doritos chips.
Mix soups, pepper, onion, tomatoes and broth together well.
Pour over chips and chicken, then slice cheese and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan (lined with foil).
Sprinkle salt over chicken; brush oil over this and coat chicken with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle lemon juice on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift all dry ingredients together and combine with first mixture.
Mix flour with raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 8-inch layer cake pans and bake in a slow oven at 300° about an hour or until cake leaves sides of pan.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift
together	flour, soda and salt.
Add sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and shortening. Blend all ingredients and mix
well. Drop
by
teaspoon
onto
ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt mary's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over ice.
This with the ice that melts makes enough to serve about 50 people.

title: poor man's raisin cake
directions: Add the raisins, hot water, sugar and Crisco together; let it come to a boil.
When cool, add cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda and flour.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown for about an hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef, then drain off the grease.
Mix sauce with one cup of water and tomato paste and boil (on back of package). Put 1/2 cup of sauce on corn shells.
Fill shells with about 2 tablespoons of meat, about 1 teaspoon of cheese and 1 teaspoon of onion.
Roll with seam down.
Place rolled shells in pan.
Cover the shells with the remaining sauce.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and about 2 tablespoons of onions.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shreveport beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion in small amount of fat.
Mix balance of ingredients and pour over meat.
Simmer 1 hour or longer.
Serve over mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: christmas coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans, 9 x 1 1/2 inches.
Beat flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, salt, shortening, milk and vanilla in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.
Beat in egg whites on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Reserve 1/2 can of juice from beans.
Combine with all other ingredients except cheese.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: party sherbet loaf(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Stir raspberry sherbet until smooth.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Level top.
Open ladyfingers.
Place over sherbet in 2 rows, end to end, cut side down.
Stir orange sherbet. Pour over ladyfingers.
Level top.
Freeze almost firm.
Whip cream.
Fold in 1 teaspoon pecan syrup and chopped pecans.
Pour over orange sherbet.
Smooth top.
Freeze.
Wrap well.
Loaf will keep at least 2 weeks and perhaps longer.

title: fancy dan pot roast
directions: Dredge meat in seasoned flour; brown in hot fat (you may not need the fat at all at this point). Drain off excess drippings. Blend onions with water, wine, catsup, garlic powder, mustard and oregano and add to meat. Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender, adding liquid as needed (mushroom juice can be added). Add mushrooms just prior to serving.

title: almond filled cookie cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch spring-form pan.
(If you use a regular round cake pan, you have to line the bottom with waxed paper, then grease.
Bake as directed; cool 30 minutes before removing from pan.)

title: sweet potato pudding *
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into buttered dish.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for about 30 minutes or until well browned.
May be served with whip cream.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients together.
Sift the remaining ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add grated rind and juice of 1 orange.
These cookies may be rolled or dropped. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Frost with a combination of powdered sugar, butter and orange juice.

title: snitches
directions: Combine everything but butterscotch chips, mix well and form into balls about 1 inch in diameter. Put on waxed paper and chill at least 30 minutes. Melt butterscotch chips in microwave on 50% power, using 30 second intervals and stirring in between. Dip balls into melted chips and use a spoon (a deep one is best) to remove and place back on waxed paper. Makes 20-30 snitches.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
